140 template <typename T>
141 constexpr uint8_t hex_to_uint(T const c)
142 {
143 if (c >= '0' && c <= '9')
144 {
145 return static_cast<uint8_t>(c - '0');
146 }
147 else if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')
148 {
149 return static_cast<uint8_t>(10 + c - 'A');
150 }
151 else if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f')
152 {
153 return static_cast<uint8_t>(10 + c - 'a');
154 }
155 else
156 {
157 throw std::invalid_argument("Character is not a hexadecimal digit");
158 }
159 }
160
161 template <typename T>
162 constexpr uint8_t hex_to_uint8(T const a, T const b)
163 {
164 return (hex_to_uint(a) << 4) | hex_to_uint(b);
165 }
166
167 constexpr uint16_t uint8_to_uint16(uint8_t a, uint8_t b)
168 {
169 return (static_cast<uint16_t>(a) << 8) | static_cast<uint16_t>(b);
170 }
171
172 constexpr uint32_t uint8_to_uint32(uint8_t a, uint8_t b, uint8_t c, uint8_t d)
173 {
174 return (static_cast<uint32_t>(uint8_to_uint16(a, b)) << 16) |
175 static_cast<uint32_t>(uint8_to_uint16(c, d));
176 }
177}

844 template <typename T, size_t LeftSize, size_t RightSize, size_t... LeftIndex, size_t... RightIndex>
845 constexpr std::array<T, LeftSize + RightSize> concat(
846 [[maybe_unused]] std::array<T, LeftSize> const& left,
847 [[maybe_unused]] std::array<T, RightSize> const& right,
848 std::index_sequence<LeftIndex...> const,
849 std::index_sequence<RightIndex...> const) noexcept
850 {

868 {

884 template <typename First, typename... Rest>
885 constexpr auto combine(First const& first, Rest const&... rest) noexcept
886 {
887 if constexpr (sizeof...(rest) == 0)
888 {
889 return to_array(first);
890 }
891 else
892 {
893 return concat(first, combine(rest...));
894 }
895 }

899 {
900 return { left[LI]..., right[RI]..., T{} };
901 }

905 {

940 constexpr std::array<uint8_t, 4> to_array(uint32_t value) noexcept
941 {
942 return { static_cast<uint8_t>(value & 0x000000ff), static_cast<uint8_t>((value & 0x0000ff00) >> 8), static_cast<uint8_t>((value & 0x00ff0000) >> 16), static_cast<uint8_t>((value & 0xff000000) >> 24) };
943 }
944
945 constexpr std::array<uint8_t, 2> to_array(uint16_t value) noexcept
946 {
947 return { static_cast<uint8_t>(value & 0x00ff), static_cast<uint8_t>((value & 0xff00) >> 8) };
948 }
949
950 constexpr auto to_array(guid const& value) noexcept
951 {
952 return combine(to_array(value.Data1), to_array(value.Data2), to_array(value.Data3),
953 std::array<uint8_t, 8>{ value.Data4[0], value.Data4[1], value.Data4[2], value.Data4[3], value.Data4[4], value.Data4[5], value.Data4[6], value.Data4[7] });
954 }

956 template <typename T>
957 constexpr T to_hex_digit(uint8_t value) noexcept
958 {
959 value &= 0xF;
960 return value < 10 ? static_cast<T>('0') + value : static_cast<T>('a') + (value - 10);
961 }
962
963 template <typename T>
964 constexpr std::array<T, 2> uint8_to_hex(uint8_t const value) noexcept
965 {
966 return { to_hex_digit<T>(value >> 4), to_hex_digit<T>(value & 0xF) };
967 }
968
969 template <typename T>
970 constexpr auto uint16_to_hex(uint16_t value) noexcept
971 {
972 return combine(uint8_to_hex<T>(static_cast<uint8_t>(value >> 8)), uint8_to_hex<T>(value & 0xFF));
973 }
974
975 template <typename T>
976 constexpr auto uint32_to_hex(uint32_t const value) noexcept
977 {
978 return combine(uint16_to_hex<T>(value >> 16), uint16_to_hex<T>(value & 0xFFFF));
979 }
980
981 template <typename T>
982 constexpr auto to_array(guid const& value) noexcept
983 {
984 return combine
985 (
986 std::array<T, 1>{'{'},
987 uint32_to_hex<T>(value.Data1), std::array<T, 1>{'-'},
988 uint16_to_hex<T>(value.Data2), std::array<T, 1>{'-'},
989 uint16_to_hex<T>(value.Data3), std::array<T, 1>{'-'},
990 uint16_to_hex<T>(value.Data4[0] << 8 | value.Data4[1]), std::array<T, 1>{'-'},
991 uint16_to_hex<T>(value.Data4[2] << 8 | value.Data4[3]),
992 uint16_to_hex<T>(value.Data4[4] << 8 | value.Data4[5]),
993 uint16_to_hex<T>(value.Data4[6] << 8 | value.Data4[7]),
994 std::array<T, 1>{'}'}
995 );
996 }
997
998 constexpr uint32_t to_guid(uint8_t a, uint8_t b, uint8_t c, uint8_t d) noexcept
999 {
1000 return (static_cast<uint32_t>(d) << 24) | (static_cast<uint32_t>(c) << 16) | (static_cast<uint32_t>(b) << 8) | static_cast<uint32_t>(a);
1001 }
1002
1003 constexpr uint16_t to_guid(uint8_t a, uint8_t b) noexcept
1004 {
1005 return (static_cast<uint32_t>(b) << 8) | static_cast<uint32_t>(a);
1006 }
1007
1008 template <size_t Size>
1009 constexpr guid to_guid(std::array<uint8_t, Size> const& arr) noexcept
1010 {
1011 return
1012 {
1013 to_guid(arr[0], arr[1], arr[2], arr[3]),
1014 to_guid(arr[4], arr[5]),
1015 to_guid(arr[6], arr[7]),
1016 { arr[8], arr[9], arr[10], arr[11], arr[12], arr[13], arr[14], arr[15] }
1017 };
1018 }

1020 constexpr uint32_t endian_swap(uint32_t value) noexcept
1021 {
1022 return (value & 0xFF000000) >> 24 | (value & 0x00FF0000) >> 8 | (value & 0x0000FF00) << 8 | (value & 0x000000FF) << 24;
1023 }
1024
1025 constexpr uint16_t endian_swap(uint16_t value) noexcept
1026 {
1027 return (value & 0xFF00) >> 8 | (value & 0x00FF) << 8;
1028 }
1029
1030 constexpr guid endian_swap(guid value) noexcept
1031 {
1032 value.Data1 = endian_swap(value.Data1);
1033 value.Data2 = endian_swap(value.Data2);
1034 value.Data3 = endian_swap(value.Data3);
1035 return value;
1036 }
1037
1038 constexpr guid set_named_guid_fields(guid value) noexcept
1039 {
1040 value.Data3 = static_cast<uint16_t>((value.Data3 & 0x0fff) | (5 << 12));
1041 value.Data4[0] = static_cast<uint8_t>((value.Data4[0] & 0x3f) | 0x80);
1042 return value;
1043 }

1045 template <typename T, size_t Size, size_t... Index>
1046 constexpr std::array<uint8_t, Size> char_to_byte_array(std::array<T, Size> const& value, std::index_sequence<Index...> const) noexcept
1047 {
1048 return { static_cast<uint8_t>(value[Index])... };
1049 }
1050
1051 constexpr auto sha1_rotl(uint8_t bits, uint32_t word) noexcept
1052 {
1053 return (word << bits) | (word >> (32 - bits));
1054 }
1055
1056 constexpr auto sha_ch(uint32_t x, uint32_t y, uint32_t z) noexcept
1057 {
1058 return (x & y) ^ ((~x) & z);
1059 }
1060
1061 constexpr auto sha_parity(uint32_t x, uint32_t y, uint32_t z) noexcept
1062 {
1063 return x ^ y ^ z;
1064 }
1065
1066 constexpr auto sha_maj(uint32_t x, uint32_t y, uint32_t z) noexcept
1067 {
1068 return (x & y) ^ (x & z) ^ (y & z);
1069 }
1070
1071 constexpr std::array<uint32_t, 5> process_msg_block(uint8_t const* input, size_t start_pos, std::array<uint32_t, 5> const& intermediate_hash) noexcept
1072 {
1073 uint32_t const K[4] = { 0x5A827999, 0x6ED9EBA1, 0x8F1BBCDC, 0xCA62C1D6 };
1074 std::array<uint32_t, 80> W = {};
1075
1076 size_t t = 0;
1077 uint32_t temp = 0;
1078
1079 for (t = 0; t < 16; t++)
1080 {
1081 W[t] = static_cast<uint32_t>(input[start_pos + t * 4]) << 24;
1082 W[t] = W[t] | static_cast<uint32_t>(input[start_pos + t * 4 + 1]) << 16;
1083 W[t] = W[t] | static_cast<uint32_t>(input[start_pos + t * 4 + 2]) << 8;
1084 W[t] = W[t] | static_cast<uint32_t>(input[start_pos + t * 4 + 3]);
1085 }
1086
1087 for (t = 16; t < 80; t++)
1088 {
1089 W[t] = sha1_rotl(1, W[t - 3] ^ W[t - 8] ^ W[t - 14] ^ W[t - 16]);
1090 }
1091
1092 uint32_t A = intermediate_hash[0];
1093 uint32_t B = intermediate_hash[1];
1094 uint32_t C = intermediate_hash[2];
1095 uint32_t D = intermediate_hash[3];
1096 uint32_t E = intermediate_hash[4];
1097
1098 for (t = 0; t < 20; t++)
1099 {
1100 temp = sha1_rotl(5, A) + sha_ch(B, C, D) + E + W[t] + K[0];
1101 E = D;
1102 D = C;
1103 C = sha1_rotl(30, B);
1104 B = A;
1105 A = temp;
1106 }
1107
1108 for (t = 20; t < 40; t++)
1109 {
1110 temp = sha1_rotl(5, A) + sha_parity(B, C, D) + E + W[t] + K[1];
1111 E = D;
1112 D = C;
1113 C = sha1_rotl(30, B);
1114 B = A;
1115 A = temp;
1116 }
1117
1118 for (t = 40; t < 60; t++)
1119 {
1120 temp = sha1_rotl(5, A) + sha_maj(B, C, D) + E + W[t] + K[2];
1121 E = D;
1122 D = C;
1123 C = sha1_rotl(30, B);
1124 B = A;
1125 A = temp;
1126 }
1127
1128 for (t = 60; t < 80; t++)
1129 {
1130 temp = sha1_rotl(5, A) + sha_parity(B, C, D) + E + W[t] + K[3];
1131 E = D;
1132 D = C;
1133 C = sha1_rotl(30, B);
1134 B = A;
1135 A = temp;
1136 }
1137
1138 return { intermediate_hash[0] + A, intermediate_hash[1] + B, intermediate_hash[2] + C, intermediate_hash[3] + D, intermediate_hash[4] + E };
1139 }
1140
1141 template <size_t Size>
1142 constexpr std::array<uint32_t, 5> process_msg_block(std::array<uint8_t, Size> const& input, size_t start_pos, std::array<uint32_t, 5> const& intermediate_hash) noexcept
1143 {
1144 return process_msg_block(input.data(), start_pos, intermediate_hash);
1145 }
1146
1147 constexpr std::array<uint8_t, 8> size_to_bytes(size_t size) noexcept
1148 {
1149 return
1150 {
1151 static_cast<uint8_t>((size & 0xff00000000000000) >> 56),
1152 static_cast<uint8_t>((size & 0x00ff000000000000) >> 48),
1153 static_cast<uint8_t>((size & 0x0000ff0000000000) >> 40),
1154 static_cast<uint8_t>((size & 0x000000ff00000000) >> 32),
1155 static_cast<uint8_t>((size & 0x00000000ff000000) >> 24),
1156 static_cast<uint8_t>((size & 0x0000000000ff0000) >> 16),
1157 static_cast<uint8_t>((size & 0x000000000000ff00) >> 8),
1158 static_cast<uint8_t>((size & 0x00000000000000ff) >> 0)
1159 };
1160 }
1161
1162 template <size_t Size, size_t RemainingSize, size_t... Index>
1163 constexpr std::array<uint8_t, RemainingSize + 1> make_remaining([[maybe_unused]] std::array<uint8_t, Size> const& input, [[maybe_unused]] size_t start_pos, std::index_sequence<Index...>) noexcept
1164 {
1165 return { input[Index + start_pos]..., 0x80 };
1166 }
1167
1168 template <size_t Size>
1169 constexpr auto make_remaining(std::array<uint8_t, Size> const& input, size_t start_pos) noexcept
1170 {
1171 constexpr auto remaining_size = Size % 64;
1172 return make_remaining<Size, remaining_size>(input, start_pos, std::make_index_sequence<remaining_size>());
1173 }
1174
1175 template <size_t InputSize, size_t RemainderSize>
1176 constexpr auto make_buffer(std::array<uint8_t, RemainderSize> const& remaining_buffer) noexcept
1177 {
1178 constexpr auto message_length = (RemainderSize + 8 <= 64) ? 64 : 64 * 2;
1179 constexpr auto padding_length = message_length - RemainderSize - 8;
1180
1181 auto padding_buffer = std::array<uint8_t, padding_length>{};
1182 auto length_buffer = size_to_bytes(InputSize * 8);
1183
1184 return combine(remaining_buffer, padding_buffer, length_buffer);
1185 }
1186
1187 template <size_t Size>
1188 constexpr std::array<uint32_t, 5> finalize_remaining_buffer(std::array<uint8_t, Size> const& input, std::array<uint32_t, 5> const& intermediate_hash) noexcept
1189 {
1190 if constexpr (Size == 64)
1191 {
1192 return process_msg_block(input, 0, intermediate_hash);
1193 }
1194 else if constexpr (Size == 64 * 2)
1195 {
1196 return process_msg_block(input, 64, process_msg_block(input, 0, intermediate_hash));
1197 }
1198 }
1199
1200 template <size_t... Index>
1201 constexpr std::array<uint8_t, 20> get_result(std::array<uint32_t, 5> const& intermediate_hash, std::index_sequence<Index...>) noexcept
1202 {
1203 return { static_cast<uint8_t>(intermediate_hash[Index >> 2] >> (8 * (3 - (Index & 0x03))))... };
1204 }
1205
1206 constexpr auto get_result(std::array<uint32_t, 5> const& intermediate_hash) noexcept
1207 {
1208 return get_result(intermediate_hash, std::make_index_sequence<20>{});
1209 }
1210
1211 template <size_t Size>
1212 constexpr auto calculate_sha1(std::array<uint8_t, Size> const& input) noexcept
1213 {
1214 std::array<uint32_t, 5> intermediate_hash{ 0x67452301, 0xEFCDAB89, 0x98BADCFE, 0x10325476, 0xC3D2E1F0 };
1215 size_t i = 0;
1216
1217 while (i + 64 <= Size)
1218 {
1219 intermediate_hash = process_msg_block(input, i, intermediate_hash);
1220 i += 64;
1221 }
1222
1223 intermediate_hash = finalize_remaining_buffer(make_buffer<Size>(make_remaining(input, i)), intermediate_hash);
1224 return get_result(intermediate_hash);
1225 }
1226
1227 template <size_t Size>
1228 constexpr guid generate_guid(std::array<char, Size> const& value) noexcept
1229 {
1230 guid namespace_guid = { 0xd57af411, 0x737b, 0xc042,{ 0xab, 0xae, 0x87, 0x8b, 0x1e, 0x16, 0xad, 0xee } };
1231
1232 auto buffer = combine(to_array(namespace_guid), char_to_byte_array(value, std::make_index_sequence<Size>()));
1233 auto hash = calculate_sha1(buffer);
1234 auto big_endian_guid = to_guid(hash);
1235 auto little_endian_guid = endian_swap(big_endian_guid);
1236 return set_named_guid_fields(little_endian_guid);
1237 }
1238
1239 template <typename TArg, typename... TRest>
1240 struct arg_collection
1241 {
1242 constexpr static auto data{ combine(to_array(signature<TArg>::data), ";", arg_collection<TRest...>::data) };
1243 };
1244
1245 template <typename TArg>
1246 struct arg_collection<TArg>
1247 {
1248 constexpr static auto data{ to_array(signature<TArg>::data) };
1249 };
1250
1251 template <typename T>
1252 struct pinterface_guid
1253 {
1254#pragma warning(suppress: 4307)
1255 static constexpr guid value{ generate_guid(signature<T>::data) };
1256 };
1257
1258 template <typename T>
1259#ifdef __clang__
1260 inline static const auto name_v
1261#else
1262#pragma warning(suppress: 4307)
1263 inline constexpr auto name_v
1264#endif
1265 {
1266 combine
1267 (
1268 to_array<wchar_t>(guid_of<T>()),
1269 std::array<wchar_t, 1>{ L'\0' }
1270 )
1271 };
1272
1273 constexpr size_t to_utf8_size(wchar_t const value) noexcept
1274 {
1275 if (value <= 0x7F)
1276 {
1277 return 1;
1278 }
1279
1280 if (value <= 0x7FF)
1281 {
1282 return 2;
1283 }
1284
1285 return 3;
1286 }
1287
1288 constexpr size_t to_utf8(wchar_t const value, char* buffer) noexcept
1289 {
1290 if (value <= 0x7F)
1291 {
1292 *buffer = static_cast<char>(value);
1293 return 1;
1294 }
1295
1296 if (value <= 0x7FF)
1297 {
1298 *buffer = static_cast<char>(0xC0 | (value >> 6));
1299 *(buffer + 1) = 0x80 | (value & 0x3F);
1300 return 2;
1301 }
1302
1303 *buffer = 0xE0 | (value >> 12);
1304 *(buffer + 1) = 0x80 | ((value >> 6) & 0x3F);
1305 *(buffer + 2) = 0x80 | (value & 0x3F);
1306 return 3;
1307 }
1308
1309 template <typename T>
1310 constexpr size_t to_utf8_size() noexcept
1311 {
1312 auto input = to_array(name_v<T>);
1313 size_t length = 0;
1314
1315 for (wchar_t const element : input)
1316 {
1317 length += to_utf8_size(element);
1318 }
1319
1320 return length;
1321 }
1322
1323 template <typename T>
1324 constexpr auto to_utf8() noexcept
1325 {
1326 auto input = to_array(name_v<T>);
1327 std::array<char, to_utf8_size<T>()> output{};
1328 size_t offset{};
1329
1330 for (wchar_t const element : input)
1331 {
1332 offset += to_utf8(element, &output[offset]);
1333 }
1334
1335 return output;
1336 }

1466{
1467 template <typename T>
1468 struct handle_type
1469 {
1470 using type = typename T::type;
1471
1472 handle_type() noexcept = default;
1473
1474 explicit handle_type(type value) noexcept : m_value(value)
1475 {
1476 }
1477
1478 handle_type(handle_type&& other) noexcept : m_value(other.detach())
1479 {
1480 }
1481
1482 handle_type& operator=(handle_type&& other) noexcept
1483 {
1484 if (this != &other)
1485 {
1486 attach(other.detach());
1487 }
1488
1489 return*this;
1490 }
1491
1492 ~handle_type() noexcept
1493 {
1494 close();
1495 }
1496
1497 void close() noexcept
1498 {
1499 if (*this)
1500 {
1501 T::close(m_value);
1502 m_value = T::invalid();
1503 }
1504 }
1505
1506 explicit operator bool() const noexcept
1507 {
1508 return T::invalid() != m_value;
1509 }
1510
1511 type get() const noexcept
1512 {
1513 return m_value;
1514 }
1515
1516 type* put() noexcept
1517 {
1518 close();
1519 return &m_value;
1520 }
1521
1522 void attach(type value) noexcept
1523 {
1524 close();
1525 *put() = value;
1526 }
1527
1528 type detach() noexcept
1529 {
1530 type value = m_value;
1531 m_value = T::invalid();
1532 return value;
1533 }
1534
1535 friend void swap(handle_type& left, handle_type& right) noexcept
1536 {
1537 std::swap(left.m_value, right.m_value);
1538 }
1539
1540 private:
1541
1542 type m_value = T::invalid();
1543 };
1544
1545 struct handle_traits
1546 {
1547 using type = void*;
1548
1549 static void close(type value) noexcept
1550 {
1551 WINRT_VERIFY_(1, WINRT_IMPL_CloseHandle(value));
1552 }
1553
1554 static constexpr type invalid() noexcept
1555 {
1556 return nullptr;
1557 }
1558 };
1559
1560 using handle = handle_type<handle_traits>;
1561
1562 struct file_handle_traits
1563 {
1564 using type = void*;
1565
1566 static void close(type value) noexcept
1567 {
1568 WINRT_VERIFY_(1, WINRT_IMPL_CloseHandle(value));
1569 }
1570
1571 static type invalid() noexcept
1572 {
1573 return reinterpret_cast<type>(-1);
1574 }
1575 };
1576
1577 using file_handle = handle_type<file_handle_traits>;
1578}

1583
1584 struct slim_mutex
1585 {
1586 slim_mutex(slim_mutex const&) = delete;
1587 slim_mutex& operator=(slim_mutex const&) = delete;
1588 slim_mutex() noexcept = default;
1589
1590 void lock() noexcept
1591 {
1592 WINRT_IMPL_AcquireSRWLockExclusive(&m_lock);
1593 }
1594
1595 void lock_shared() noexcept
1596 {
1597 WINRT_IMPL_AcquireSRWLockShared(&m_lock);
1598 }
1599
1600 bool try_lock() noexcept
1601 {
1602 return 0 != WINRT_IMPL_TryAcquireSRWLockExclusive(&m_lock);
1603 }
1604
1605 bool try_lock_shared() noexcept
1606 {
1607 return 0 != WINRT_IMPL_TryAcquireSRWLockShared(&m_lock);
1608 }
1609
1610 void unlock() noexcept
1611 {
1612 WINRT_IMPL_ReleaseSRWLockExclusive(&m_lock);
1613 }
1614
1615 void unlock_shared() noexcept
1616 {
1617 WINRT_IMPL_ReleaseSRWLockShared(&m_lock);
1618 }
1619
1620 private:
1621 friend slim_condition_variable;
1622
1623 auto get() noexcept
1624 {
1625 return &m_lock;
1626 }
1627
1628 impl::srwlock m_lock{};
1629 };
1630
1631 struct slim_lock_guard
1632 {
1633 explicit slim_lock_guard(slim_mutex& m) noexcept :
1634 m_mutex(m)
1635 {
1636 m_mutex.lock();
1637 }
1638
1639 slim_lock_guard(slim_lock_guard const&) = delete;
1640
1641 ~slim_lock_guard() noexcept
1642 {
1643 m_mutex.unlock();
1644 }
1645
1646 private:
1647 slim_mutex& m_mutex;
1648 };
1649
1650 struct slim_shared_lock_guard
1651 {
1652 explicit slim_shared_lock_guard(slim_mutex& m) noexcept :
1653 m_mutex(m)
1654 {
1655 m_mutex.lock_shared();
1656 }
1657
1658 slim_shared_lock_guard(slim_shared_lock_guard const&) = delete;
1659
1660 ~slim_shared_lock_guard() noexcept
1661 {
1662 m_mutex.unlock_shared();
1663 }
1664
1665 private:
1666 slim_mutex& m_mutex;
1667 };
1668
1669 struct slim_condition_variable
1670 {
1671 slim_condition_variable(slim_condition_variable const&) = delete;
1672 slim_condition_variable const& operator=(slim_condition_variable const&) = delete;
1673 slim_condition_variable() noexcept = default;
1674
1675 template <typename T>
1676 void wait(slim_mutex& x, T predicate)
1677 {
1678 while (!predicate())
1679 {
1680 WINRT_VERIFY(WINRT_IMPL_SleepConditionVariableSRW(&m_cv, x.get(), 0xFFFFFFFF /*INFINITE*/, 0));
1681 }
1682 }
1683
1684 template <typename T>
1685 bool wait_for(slim_mutex& x, std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::duration const timeout, T predicate)
1686 {
1687 auto const until = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now() + timeout;
1688
1689 while (!predicate())
1690 {
1691 auto const milliseconds = std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::milliseconds>(until - std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now()).count();
1692
1693 if (milliseconds <= 0)
1694 {
1695 return false;
1696 }
1697
1698 if (!WINRT_IMPL_SleepConditionVariableSRW(&m_cv, x.get(), static_cast<uint32_t>(milliseconds), 0))
1699 {
1700 return predicate();
1701 }
1702 }
1703
1704 return true;
1705 }
1706
1707 void notify_one() noexcept
1708 {
1709 WINRT_IMPL_WakeConditionVariable(&m_cv);
1710 }
1711
1712 void notify_all() noexcept
1713 {
1714 WINRT_IMPL_WakeAllConditionVariable(&m_cv);
1715 }
1716
1717 private:
1718 impl::condition_variable m_cv{};
1719 };
1720}

1891 {
1892 bool is_agile{ true };
1893 uint32_t requests{ 0 };
1894 };
1895
1896 struct diagnostics_info
1897 {
1898 std::map<std::wstring_view, uint32_t> queries;
1899 std::map<std::wstring_view, factory_diagnostics_info> factories;
1900 };
1901
1902 struct diagnostics_cache
1903 {
1904 template <typename T>
1905 void add_query()
1906 {
1907 slim_lock_guard const guard(m_lock);
1908 ++m_info.queries[name_of<T>()];
1909 }
1910
1911 template <typename T>
1912 void add_factory()
1913 {
1914 slim_lock_guard const guard(m_lock);
1915 factory_diagnostics_info& factory = m_info.factories[name_of<T>()];
1916 ++factory.requests;
1917 }
1918
1919 template <typename T>
1920 void non_agile_factory()
1921 {
1922 slim_lock_guard const guard(m_lock);
1923 factory_diagnostics_info& factory = m_info.factories[name_of<T>()];
1924 factory.is_agile = false;
1925 }
1926
1927 auto get()
1928 {
1929 slim_lock_guard const guard(m_lock);
1930 return m_info;
1931 }
1932
1933 auto detach()
1934 {
1935 slim_lock_guard const guard(m_lock);
1936 return std::move(m_info);
1937 }
1938
1939 private:
1940
1941 slim_mutex m_lock;
1942 diagnostics_info m_info;
1943 };

1946 {

1953 template <typename T>
1954 using com_ref = std::conditional_t<std::is_base_of_v<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown, T>, T, com_ptr<T>>;
1955
1956 template <typename T, std::enable_if_t<is_implements_v<T>, int> = 0>
1957 com_ref<T> wrap_as_result(void* result)
1958 {
1959 return { &static_cast<produce<T, typename default_interface<T>::type>*>(result)->shim(), take_ownership_from_abi };
1960 }
1961
1962 template <typename T, std::enable_if_t<!is_implements_v<T>, int> = 0>
1963 com_ref<T> wrap_as_result(void* result)
1964 {
1965 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
1966 }
1967
1968#ifdef WINRT_IMPL_IUNKNOWN_DEFINED
1969 template <typename T>
1970 struct is_com_interface : std::disjunction<std::is_base_of<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown, T>, std::is_base_of<unknown_abi, T>, is_implements<T>, std::is_base_of<::IUnknown, T>> {};
1971#else
1972 template <typename T>
1973 struct is_com_interface : std::disjunction<std::is_base_of<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown, T>, std::is_base_of<unknown_abi, T>, is_implements<T>> {};
1974#endif
1975
1976 template <typename T>
1977 inline constexpr bool is_com_interface_v = is_com_interface<T>::value;
1978
1979 // You must include <winrt/Windows.Foundation.h> to use this overload.
1980 template <typename To, typename From, std::enable_if_t<!is_com_interface_v<To>, int> = 0>
1981 auto as(From* ptr);
1982
1983 template <typename To, typename From, std::enable_if_t<is_com_interface_v<To>, int> = 0>
1984 com_ref<To> as(From* ptr)
1985 {
1986#ifdef WINRT_DIAGNOSTICS
1987 get_diagnostics_info().add_query<To>();
1988#endif
1989
1990 if (!ptr)
1991 {
1992 return nullptr;
1993 }
1994
1995 void* result{};
1996 check_hresult(ptr->QueryInterface(guid_of<To>(), &result));
1997 return wrap_as_result<To>(result);
1998 }
1999
2000 // You must include <winrt/Windows.Foundation.h> to use this overload.
2001 template <typename To, typename From, std::enable_if_t<!is_com_interface_v<To>, int> = 0>
2002 auto try_as(From* ptr) noexcept;
2003
2004 template <typename To, typename From, std::enable_if_t<is_com_interface_v<To>, int> = 0>
2005 com_ref<To> try_as(From* ptr) noexcept
2006 {
2007#ifdef WINRT_DIAGNOSTICS
2008 get_diagnostics_info().add_query<To>();
2009#endif
2010
2011 if (!ptr)
2012 {
2013 return nullptr;
2014 }
2015
2016 void* result{};
2017 ptr->QueryInterface(guid_of<To>(), &result);
2018 return wrap_as_result<To>(result);
2019 }

2024 struct IUnknown
2025 {
2026 IUnknown() noexcept = default;
2027 IUnknown(std::nullptr_t) noexcept {}

2029
2030 IUnknown(void* ptr, take_ownership_from_abi_t) noexcept : m_ptr(static_cast<impl::unknown_abi*>(ptr))
2031 {
2032 }
2033
2034 IUnknown(IUnknown const& other) noexcept : m_ptr(other.m_ptr)
2035 {
2036 add_ref();
2037 }
2038
2039 IUnknown(IUnknown&& other) noexcept : m_ptr(std::exchange(other.m_ptr, {}))
2040 {
2041 }
2042
2043 ~IUnknown() noexcept
2044 {
2045 release_ref();
2046 }
2047
2048 IUnknown& operator=(IUnknown const& other) noexcept
2049 {
2050 if (this != &other)
2051 {
2052 release_ref();
2053 m_ptr = other.m_ptr;
2054 add_ref();
2055 }
2056
2057 return*this;
2058 }
2059
2060 IUnknown& operator=(IUnknown&& other) noexcept
2061 {
2062 if (this != &other)
2063 {
2064 release_ref();
2065 m_ptr = std::exchange(other.m_ptr, {});
2066 }
2067
2068 return*this;
2069 }
2070
2071 explicit operator bool() const noexcept
2072 {
2073 return nullptr != m_ptr;
2074 }
2075
2076 IUnknown& operator=(std::nullptr_t) noexcept
2077 {
2078 release_ref();
2079 return*this;
2080 }
2081
2082 template <typename To>

2084 {
2085 return impl::as<To>(m_ptr);
2086 }
2087

2090 {
2091 return impl::try_as<To>(m_ptr);
2092 }

2096 {
2097 to = as<impl::wrapped_type_t<To>>();
2098 }

2100 template <typename To>
2101 bool try_as(To& to) const noexcept
2102 {
2103 if constexpr (impl::is_com_interface_v<To> || !std::is_same_v<To, impl::wrapped_type_t<To>>)
2104 {
2105 to = try_as<impl::wrapped_type_t<To>>();
2106 return static_cast<bool>(to);
2107 }
2108 else
2109 {
2110 auto result = try_as<To>();
2111 to = result.has_value() ? result.value() : impl::empty_value<To>();
2112 return result.has_value();
2113 }
2114 }

2116 hresult as(guid const& id, void** result) const noexcept
2117 {
2118 return m_ptr->QueryInterface(id, result);
2119 }

2122 {
2123 std::swap(left.m_ptr, right.m_ptr);
2124 }

2128 void add_ref() const noexcept
2129 {
2130 if (m_ptr)
2131 {
2132 m_ptr->AddRef();
2133 }
2134 }
2135
2136 void release_ref() noexcept
2137 {
2138 if (m_ptr)
2139 {
2140 unconditional_release_ref();
2141 }
2142 }
2143
2144 WINRT_IMPL_NOINLINE void unconditional_release_ref() noexcept
2145 {
2146 std::exchange(m_ptr, {})->Release();
2147 }

2149 impl::unknown_abi* m_ptr{};
2150 };

2262 inline bool operator==(IUnknown const& left, IUnknown const& right) noexcept
2263 {
2264 if (get_abi(left) == get_abi(right))
2265 {
2266 return true;
2267 }
2268 if (!left || !right)
2269 {
2270 return false;
2271 }
2272 return get_abi(left.try_as<IUnknown>()) == get_abi(right.try_as<IUnknown>());
2273 }
2274
2275 inline bool operator!=(IUnknown const& left, IUnknown const& right) noexcept
2276 {
2277 return !(left == right);
2278 }
2279
2280 inline bool operator<(IUnknown const& left, IUnknown const& right) noexcept
2281 {
2282 if (get_abi(left) == get_abi(right))
2283 {
2284 return false;
2285 }
2286 if (!left || !right)
2287 {
2288 return get_abi(left) < get_abi(right);
2289 }
2290 return get_abi(left.try_as<IUnknown>()) < get_abi(right.try_as<IUnknown>());
2291 }
2292
2293 inline bool operator>(IUnknown const& left, IUnknown const& right) noexcept
2294 {
2295 return right < left;
2296 }
2297
2298 inline bool operator<=(IUnknown const& left, IUnknown const& right) noexcept
2299 {
2300 return !(right < left);
2301 }
2302
2303 inline bool operator>=(IUnknown const& left, IUnknown const& right) noexcept
2304 {
2305 return !(left < right);
2306 }

2557 impl::capture_to<T>(&result, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
2558 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
2559 }
2560
2561 template <typename T, typename...Args>
2562 impl::com_ref<T> capture(Args&& ...args)
2563 {
2564 void* result{};
2565 check_hresult(impl::capture_to<T>(&result, std::forward<Args>(args)...));
2566 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
2567 }

2571 {
2572 return object.get();
2573 }

2589 {

2591 }

2595 {

2671 struct atomic_ref_count
2672 {
2673 atomic_ref_count() noexcept = default;
2674
2675 explicit atomic_ref_count(uint32_t count) noexcept : m_count(count)
2676 {
2677 }
2678
2679 uint32_t operator=(uint32_t count) noexcept
2680 {
2681 return m_count = count;
2682 }
2683
2684 uint32_t operator++() noexcept
2685 {
2686 return m_count.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_relaxed) + 1;
2687 }
2688
2689 uint32_t operator--() noexcept
2690 {
2691 auto const remaining = m_count.fetch_sub(1, std::memory_order_release) - 1;
2692
2693 if (remaining == 0)
2694 {
2695 std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_acquire);
2696 }
2697 else if (remaining < 0)
2698 {
2699 abort();
2700 }
2701
2702 return remaining;
2703 }
2704
2705 operator uint32_t() const noexcept
2706 {
2707 return m_count;
2708 }
2709
2710 private:
2711
2712 std::atomic<int32_t> m_count;
2713 };
2714
2715 constexpr uint32_t hstring_reference_flag{ 1 };
2716
2717 struct hstring_header
2718 {
2719 uint32_t flags;
2720 uint32_t length;
2721 uint32_t padding1;
2722 uint32_t padding2;
2723 wchar_t const* ptr;
2724 };
2725
2726 struct shared_hstring_header : hstring_header
2727 {
2728 atomic_ref_count count;
2729 wchar_t buffer[1];
2730 };
2731
2732 inline void release_hstring(hstring_header* handle) noexcept
2733 {
2734 WINRT_ASSERT((handle->flags & hstring_reference_flag) == 0);
2735
2736 if (0 == --static_cast<shared_hstring_header*>(handle)->count)
2737 {
2738 WINRT_IMPL_HeapFree(WINRT_IMPL_GetProcessHeap(), 0, handle);
2739 }
2740 }
2741
2742 inline shared_hstring_header* precreate_hstring_on_heap(uint32_t length)
2743 {
2744 WINRT_ASSERT(length != 0);
2745 uint64_t bytes_required = static_cast<uint64_t>(sizeof(shared_hstring_header)) + static_cast<uint64_t>(sizeof(wchar_t)) * static_cast<uint64_t>(length);
2746
2747 if (bytes_required > UINT_MAX)
2748 {
2749 throw std::invalid_argument("length");
2750 }
2751
2752 auto header = static_cast<shared_hstring_header*>(WINRT_IMPL_HeapAlloc(WINRT_IMPL_GetProcessHeap(), 0, static_cast<std::size_t>(bytes_required)));
2753
2754 if (!header)
2755 {
2756 throw std::bad_alloc();
2757 }
2758
2759 header->flags = 0;
2760 header->length = length;
2761 header->ptr = header->buffer;
2762 header->count = 1;
2763 header->buffer[length] = 0;
2764 return header;
2765 }
2766
2767 inline hstring_header* create_hstring_on_heap(wchar_t const* value, uint32_t length)
2768 {
2769 if (!length)
2770 {
2771 return nullptr;
2772 }
2773
2774 auto header = precreate_hstring_on_heap(length);
2775 memcpy_s(header->buffer, sizeof(wchar_t) * length, value, sizeof(wchar_t) * length);
2776 return header;
2777 }
2778
2779 inline void create_hstring_on_stack(hstring_header& header, wchar_t const* value, uint32_t length) noexcept
2780 {
2781 WINRT_ASSERT(value);
2782 WINRT_ASSERT(length != 0);
2783
2784 if (value[length] != 0)
2785 {
2786 abort();
2787 }
2788
2789 header.flags = hstring_reference_flag;
2790 header.length = length;
2791 header.ptr = value;
2792 }
2793
2794 inline hstring_header* duplicate_hstring(hstring_header* handle)
2795 {
2796 if (!handle)
2797 {
2798 return nullptr;
2799 }
2800 else if ((handle->flags & hstring_reference_flag) == 0)
2801 {
2802 ++static_cast<shared_hstring_header*>(handle)->count;
2803 return handle;
2804 }
2805 else
2806 {
2807 return create_hstring_on_heap(handle->ptr, handle->length);
2808 }
2809 }
2810
2811 struct hstring_traits
2812 {
2813 using type = hstring_header*;
2814
2815 static void close(type value) noexcept
2816 {
2817 release_hstring(value);
2818 }
2819
2820 static constexpr type invalid() noexcept
2821 {
2822 return nullptr;
2823 }
2824 };
2825}

3195 template <typename T>
3196 inline hstring hstring_convert(T value)
3197 {
3198 static_assert(std::is_arithmetic_v<T>);
3199 char temp[32];
3200 std::to_chars_result result;
3201 if constexpr (std::is_integral_v<T>)
3202 {
3203 result = std::to_chars(std::begin(temp), std::end(temp), value);
3204 }
3205 else
3206 {
3207 // Floating point
3208 result = std::to_chars(std::begin(temp), std::end(temp), value, std::chars_format::general);
3209 }
3210 WINRT_ASSERT(result.ec == std::errc{});
3211 wchar_t buffer[32];
3212 auto end = std::copy(std::begin(temp), result.ptr, buffer);
3213 return hstring{ std::wstring_view{ buffer, static_cast<std::size_t>(end - buffer)} };
3214 }

3312 hstring to_hstring(T const& value)
3313 {

3315 int const size = WINRT_IMPL_MultiByteToWideChar(65001 /*CP_UTF8*/, 0, view.data(), static_cast<int32_t>(view.size()), nullptr, 0);
3316

3318 {
3319 return{};

3323 WINRT_VERIFY_(size, WINRT_IMPL_MultiByteToWideChar(65001 /*CP_UTF8*/, 0, view.data(), static_cast<int32_t>(view.size()), result.data(), size));
3324 return result.to_hstring();

3333 return{};

3374 return *reinterpret_cast<winrt::hstring const*>(this);
3375 }
3376
3377 private:
3378 void create_string_reference(wchar_t const* const data, size_t size) noexcept
3379 {
3380 WINRT_ASSERT(size < UINT_MAX);
3381 auto size32 = static_cast<uint32_t>(size);
3382
3383 if (size32 == 0)
3384 {
3385 m_handle = nullptr;
3386 }
3387 else
3388 {
3389 impl::create_hstring_on_stack(m_header, data, size32);
3390 m_handle = &m_header;
3391 }
3392 }
3393
3394 void* m_handle;
3395 impl::hstring_header m_header;
3396 };
3397
3398 inline void* get_abi(hstring const& object) noexcept
3399 {
3400 return *(void**)(&object);
3401 }
3402}

3505namespace winrt::impl
3506{
3507 inline hstring concat_hstring(std::wstring_view const& left, std::wstring_view const& right)
3508 {
3509 auto size = static_cast<uint32_t>(left.size() + right.size());
3510 if (size == 0)
3511 {
3512 return{};
3513 }
3514 hstring_builder text(size);
3515 memcpy_s(text.data(), left.size() * sizeof(wchar_t), left.data(), left.size() * sizeof(wchar_t));
3516 memcpy_s(text.data() + left.size(), right.size() * sizeof(wchar_t), right.data(), right.size() * sizeof(wchar_t));
3517 return text.to_hstring();
3518 }
3519}

3593 m_size(size)

3779 static_assert(!std::is_same_v<C, bool>, "Cannot use std::vector<bool> as an array_view. Consider std::array or std::unique_ptr<bool[]>.");
3780 return value.data();

3797 template <typename T>
3798 struct com_array : array_view<T>
3799 {
3800 using typename array_view<T>::value_type;
3801 using typename array_view<T>::size_type;
3802 using typename array_view<T>::reference;
3803 using typename array_view<T>::const_reference;
3804 using typename array_view<T>::pointer;
3805 using typename array_view<T>::const_pointer;
3806 using typename array_view<T>::iterator;
3807 using typename array_view<T>::const_iterator;
3808 using typename array_view<T>::reverse_iterator;
3809 using typename array_view<T>::const_reverse_iterator;
3810
3811 com_array(com_array const&) = delete;
3812 com_array& operator=(com_array const&) = delete;
3813
3814 com_array() noexcept = default;
3815
3816 explicit com_array(size_type const count) :
3817 com_array(count, value_type())
3818 {}
3819
3820 com_array(void* ptr, uint32_t const count, take_ownership_from_abi_t) noexcept :
3821 array_view<T>(static_cast<value_type*>(ptr), static_cast<value_type*>(ptr) + count)
3822 {
3823 }
3824
3825 com_array(size_type const count, value_type const& value)
3826 {
3827 alloc(count);
3828 std::uninitialized_fill_n(this->m_data, count, value);
3829 }
3830
3831 template <typename InIt, typename = std::void_t<typename std::iterator_traits<InIt>::difference_type>>
3832 com_array(InIt first, InIt last)
3833 {
3834 alloc(static_cast<size_type>(std::distance(first, last)));
3835 std::uninitialized_copy(first, last, this->begin());
3836 }
3837
3838 template <typename U>
3839 explicit com_array(std::vector<U> const& value) :
3840 com_array(value.begin(), value.end())
3841 {}
3842
3843 template <typename U, size_t N>
3844 explicit com_array(std::array<U, N> const& value) :
3845 com_array(value.begin(), value.end())
3846 {}
3847
3848 template <typename U, size_t N>
3849 explicit com_array(U const(&value)[N]) :
3850 com_array(value, value + N)
3851 {}
3852
3853 com_array(std::initializer_list<value_type> value) :
3854 com_array(value.begin(), value.end())
3855 {}
3856
3857 template <typename U, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_convertible_v<U, T>>>
3858 com_array(std::initializer_list<U> value) :
3859 com_array(value.begin(), value.end())
3860 {}
3861
3862 com_array(com_array&& other) noexcept :
3863 array_view<T>(other.m_data, other.m_size)
3864 {
3865 other.m_data = nullptr;
3866 other.m_size = 0;
3867 }
3868
3869 com_array& operator=(com_array&& other) noexcept
3870 {
3871 clear();
3872 this->m_data = other.m_data;
3873 this->m_size = other.m_size;
3874 other.m_data = nullptr;
3875 other.m_size = 0;
3876 return*this;
3877 }
3878
3879 ~com_array() noexcept
3880 {
3881 clear();
3882 }
3883
3884 void clear() noexcept
3885 {
3886 if (this->m_data == nullptr) { return; }
3887
3888 std::destroy(this->begin(), this->end());
3889
3890 WINRT_IMPL_CoTaskMemFree(this->m_data);
3891 this->m_data = nullptr;
3892 this->m_size = 0;
3893 }
3894
3895 friend void swap(com_array& left, com_array& right) noexcept
3896 {
3897 std::swap(left.m_data, right.m_data);
3898 std::swap(left.m_size, right.m_size);
3899 }
3900
3901 private:
3902
3903 void alloc(size_type const size)
3904 {
3905 WINRT_ASSERT(this->empty());
3906
3907 if (0 != size)
3908 {
3909 this->m_data = static_cast<value_type*>(WINRT_IMPL_CoTaskMemAlloc(size * sizeof(value_type)));
3910
3911 if (this->m_data == nullptr)
3912 {
3913 throw std::bad_alloc();
3914 }
3915
3916 this->m_size = size;
3917 }
3918 }
3919 };

3930 {
3931 template <typename T, typename U>
3932 inline constexpr bool array_comparable = std::is_same_v<std::remove_cv_t<T>, std::remove_cv_t<U>>;
3933 }
3934
3935 template <typename T, typename U,
3936 std::enable_if_t<impl::array_comparable<T, U>, int> = 0>
3937 bool operator==(array_view<T> const& left, array_view<U> const& right) noexcept
3938 {
3939 return std::equal(left.begin(), left.end(), right.begin(), right.end());
3940 }
3941
3942 template <typename T, typename U,
3943 std::enable_if_t<impl::array_comparable<T, U>, int> = 0>
3944 bool operator<(array_view<T> const& left, array_view<U> const& right) noexcept
3945 {
3946 return std::lexicographical_compare(left.begin(), left.end(), right.begin(), right.end());
3947 }
3948
3949 template <typename T, typename U, std::enable_if_t<impl::array_comparable<T, U>, int> = 0>
3950 bool operator!=(array_view<T> const& left, array_view<U> const& right) noexcept { return !(left == right); }
3951 template <typename T, typename U,std::enable_if_t<impl::array_comparable<T, U>, int> = 0>
3952 bool operator>(array_view<T> const& left, array_view<U> const& right) noexcept { return right < left; }
3953 template <typename T, typename U,std::enable_if_t<impl::array_comparable<T, U>, int> = 0>
3954 bool operator<=(array_view<T> const& left, array_view<U> const& right) noexcept { return !(right < left); }
3955 template <typename T, typename U, std::enable_if_t<impl::array_comparable<T, U>, int> = 0>
3956 bool operator>=(array_view<T> const& left, array_view<U> const& right) noexcept { return !(left < right); }
3957
3958 template <typename T>
3959 auto get_abi(array_view<T> object) noexcept
3960 {
3961 auto data = object.size() ? object.data() : (T*)alignof(T);
3962
3963 if constexpr (std::is_base_of_v<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown, T>)
3964 {
3965 return (void**)data;
3966 }
3967 else
3968 {
3969 return reinterpret_cast<impl::arg_out<std::remove_const_t<T>>>(const_cast<std::remove_const_t<T>*>(data));
3970 }
3971 }
3972
3973 template <typename T>
3974 auto put_abi(array_view<T> object) noexcept
3975 {
3976 if constexpr (!std::is_trivially_destructible_v<T>)
3977 {
3978 std::fill(object.begin(), object.end(), impl::empty_value<T>());
3979 }
3980
3981 return get_abi(object);
3982 }
3983
3984 template<typename T>
3985 auto put_abi(com_array<T>& object) noexcept
3986 {
3987 object.clear();
3988 return reinterpret_cast<impl::arg_out<T>*>(&object);
3989 }
3990
3991 template <typename T>
3992 auto detach_abi(com_array<T>& object) noexcept
3993 {
3994 std::pair<uint32_t, impl::arg_out<T>> result(object.size(), *reinterpret_cast<impl::arg_out<T>*>(&object));
3995 memset(&object, 0, sizeof(com_array<T>));
3996 return result;
3997 }
3998
3999 template <typename T>
4000 auto detach_abi(com_array<T>&& object) noexcept
4001 {
4002 return detach_abi(object);
4003 }
4004}

4014 {}

4017 {
4018 WINRT_ASSERT(m_value.data() || (!m_value.data() && m_size == 0));
4019 *reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t*>(&m_value) + 1) = m_size;
4020 }

4023 {

4044 template <typename T>
4045 struct com_array_proxy
4046 {
4047 com_array_proxy(uint32_t* size, winrt::impl::arg_out<T>* value) noexcept : m_size(size), m_value(value)
4048 {}
4049
4050 ~com_array_proxy() noexcept
4051 {
4052 std::tie(*m_size, *m_value) = detach_abi(m_temp);
4053 }
4054
4055 operator com_array<T>&() noexcept
4056 {
4057 return m_temp;
4058 }
4059
4060 com_array_proxy(com_array_proxy const&) noexcept
4061 {
4062 // A Visual C++ compiler bug (550631) requires the copy constructor even though it is never called.
4063 WINRT_ASSERT(false);
4064 }
4065
4066 private:
4067
4068 uint32_t* m_size;
4069 arg_out<T>* m_value;
4070 com_array<T> m_temp;
4071 };
4072}

4106 template <typename T>
4107 struct weak_ref
4108 {
4109 weak_ref(std::nullptr_t = nullptr) noexcept {}
4110
4111 weak_ref(impl::com_ref<T> const& object)
4112 {
4113 if (object)
4114 {
4115 if constexpr(impl::is_implements_v<T>)
4116 {
4117 m_ref = std::move(object->get_weak().m_ref);
4118 }
4119 else
4120 {
4121 // An access violation (crash) on the following line means that the object does not support weak references.
4122 // Avoid using weak_ref/auto_revoke with such objects.
4123 check_hresult(object.template try_as<impl::IWeakReferenceSource>()->GetWeakReference(m_ref.put()));
4124 }
4125 }
4126 }
4127
4128 [[nodiscard]] impl::com_ref<T> get() const noexcept
4129 {
4130 if (!m_ref)
4131 {
4132 return nullptr;
4133 }
4134
4135 if constexpr(impl::is_implements_v<T>)
4136 {
4137 impl::com_ref<default_interface<T>> temp;
4138 m_ref->Resolve(guid_of<T>(), put_abi(temp));
4139 void* result = get_self<T>(temp);
4140 detach_abi(temp);
4141 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
4142 }
4143 else
4144 {
4145 void* result{};
4146 m_ref->Resolve(guid_of<T>(), &result);
4147 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
4148 }
4149 }
4150
4151 auto put() noexcept
4152 {
4153 return m_ref.put();
4154 }
4155
4156 explicit operator bool() const noexcept
4157 {
4158 return static_cast<bool>(m_ref);
4159 }
4160
4161 private:
4162
4163 com_ptr<impl::IWeakReference> m_ref;
4164 };
4165
4166 template<typename T> weak_ref(T const&)->weak_ref<impl::wrapped_type_t<T>>;
4167
4168 template<typename T>
4169 struct impl::abi<weak_ref<T>> : impl::abi<com_ptr<impl::IWeakReference>>
4170 {
4171 };
4172
4173 template <typename T>
4174 inline bool operator==(weak_ref<T> const& left, weak_ref<T> const& right) noexcept
4175 {
4176 return get_abi(left) == get_abi(right);
4177 }
4178
4179 template <typename T>
4180 inline bool operator==(weak_ref<T> const& left, std::nullptr_t) noexcept
4181 {
4182 return get_abi(left) == nullptr;
4183 }
4184
4185 template <typename T>
4186 inline bool operator==(std::nullptr_t, weak_ref<T> const& right) noexcept
4187 {
4188 return nullptr == get_abi(right);
4189 }
4190
4191 template <typename T>
4192 inline bool operator!=(weak_ref<T> const& left, weak_ref<T> const& right) noexcept
4193 {
4194 return !(left == right);
4195 }
4196
4197 template <typename T>
4198 inline bool operator!=(weak_ref<T> const& left, std::nullptr_t) noexcept
4199 {
4200 return !(left == nullptr);
4201 }
4202
4203 template <typename T>
4204 inline bool operator!=(std::nullptr_t, weak_ref<T> const& right) noexcept
4205 {
4206 return !(nullptr == right);
4207 }
4208
4209 template <typename T>
4210 weak_ref<impl::wrapped_type_t<T>> make_weak(T const& object)
4211 {
4212 return object;
4213 }
4214}

4218#if defined (WINRT_NO_MODULE_LOCK)
4219
4220 // Defining WINRT_NO_MODULE_LOCK is appropriate for apps (executables) that don't implement something like DllCanUnloadNow
4221 // and can thus avoid the synchronization overhead imposed by the default module lock.
4222
4223 constexpr auto get_module_lock() noexcept
4224 {
4225 struct lock
4226 {
4227 constexpr uint32_t operator++() noexcept
4228 {
4229 return 1;
4230 }
4231
4232 constexpr uint32_t operator--() noexcept
4233 {
4234 return 0;
4235 }
4236 };
4237
4238 return lock{};
4239 }
4240
4241#elif defined (WINRT_CUSTOM_MODULE_LOCK)
4242
4243 // When WINRT_CUSTOM_MODULE_LOCK is defined, you must provide an implementation of winrt::get_module_lock()
4244 // that returns an object that implements operator++ and operator--.
4245
4246#else
4247
4248 // This is the default implementation for use with DllCanUnloadNow.
4249
4250 inline impl::atomic_ref_count& get_module_lock() noexcept
4251 {
4252 static impl::atomic_ref_count s_lock;
4253 return s_lock;
4254 }
4255
4256#endif
4257}

4263
4264 template<>
4265 struct module_lock_updater<true>
4266 {
4267 module_lock_updater() noexcept
4268 {
4269 ++get_module_lock();
4270 }
4271
4272 ~module_lock_updater() noexcept
4273 {
4274 --get_module_lock();
4275 }
4276 };

4299 {
4300 *object = static_cast<IAgileReference*>(this);
4301 AddRef();
4302 return 0;
4303 }
4304
4305 *object = nullptr;
4306 return error_no_interface;

4310 {
4311 return ++m_references;
4312 }
4313

4315 {
4316 auto const remaining = --m_references;
4317
4318 if (remaining == 0)
4319 {
4320 delete this;
4321 }
4322
4323 return remaining;
4324 }

4327 {

4329 }

4337
4338 template <typename F, typename L>
4339 void load_runtime_function(wchar_t const* library, char const* name, F& result, L fallback) noexcept
4340 {
4341 if (result)
4342 {
4343 return;
4344 }
4345
4346 result = reinterpret_cast<F>(WINRT_IMPL_GetProcAddress(WINRT_IMPL_LoadLibraryW(library), name));
4347
4348 if (result)
4349 {
4350 return;
4351 }
4352
4353 result = fallback;
4354 }
4355
4356 inline int32_t __stdcall fallback_RoGetAgileReference(uint32_t, winrt::guid const& iid, void* object, void** reference) noexcept
4357 {
4358 *reference = nullptr;
4359 static constexpr guid git_clsid{ 0x00000323, 0x0000, 0x0000, { 0xC0,0x00,0x00,0x00,0x00,0x00,0x00,0x46 } };
4360
4361 com_ptr<IGlobalInterfaceTable> git;
4362 hresult hr = WINRT_IMPL_CoCreateInstance(git_clsid, nullptr, 1 /*CLSCTX_INPROC_SERVER*/, guid_of<IGlobalInterfaceTable>(), git.put_void());
4363
4364 if (hr < 0)
4365 {
4366 return hr;
4367 }
4368
4369 uint32_t cookie{};
4370 hr = git->RegisterInterfaceInGlobal(object, iid, &cookie);
4371
4372 if (hr < 0)
4373 {
4374 return hr;
4375 }
4376
4377 *reference = new agile_ref_fallback(std::move(git), cookie);
4378 return 0;
4379 }
4380
4381 inline hresult get_agile_reference(winrt::guid const& iid, void* object, void** reference) noexcept
4382 {
4383 static int32_t(__stdcall * handler)(uint32_t options, winrt::guid const& iid, void* object, void** reference) noexcept;
4384 load_runtime_function(L"combase.dll", "RoGetAgileReference", handler, fallback_RoGetAgileReference);
4385 return handler(0, iid, object, reference);
4386 }
4387}

4461 struct bstr_traits
4462 {
4463 using type = wchar_t*;
4464
4465 static void close(type value) noexcept
4466 {
4467 WINRT_IMPL_SysFreeString(value);
4468 }
4469
4470 static constexpr type invalid() noexcept
4471 {
4472 return nullptr;
4473 }
4474 };
4475
4476 using bstr_handle = handle_type<bstr_traits>;
4477
4478 inline hstring trim_hresult_message(wchar_t const* const message, uint32_t size) noexcept
4479 {
4480 wchar_t const* back = message + size - 1;
4481
4482 while (size&& iswspace(*back))
4483 {
4484 --size;
4485 --back;
4486 }
4487
4488 return { message, size };
4489 }
4490
4491 inline hstring message_from_hresult(hresult code) noexcept
4492 {
4493 handle_type<impl::heap_traits> message;
4494
4495 uint32_t const size = WINRT_IMPL_FormatMessageW(0x00001300, // FORMAT_MESSAGE_ALLOCATE_BUFFER | FORMAT_MESSAGE_FROM_SYSTEM | FORMAT_MESSAGE_IGNORE_INSERTS
4496 nullptr,
4497 code,
4498 0x00000400, // MAKELANGID(LANG_NEUTRAL, SUBLANG_DEFAULT)
4499 reinterpret_cast<wchar_t*>(message.put()),
4500 0,
4501 nullptr);
4502
4503 return trim_hresult_message(message.get(), size);
4504 }
4505
4506 constexpr int32_t hresult_from_win32(uint32_t const x) noexcept
4507 {
4508 return (int32_t)(x) <= 0 ? (int32_t)(x) : (int32_t)(((x) & 0x0000FFFF) | (7 << 16) | 0x80000000);
4509 }
4510
4511 constexpr int32_t hresult_from_nt(uint32_t const x) noexcept
4512 {
4513 return ((int32_t)((x) | 0x10000000));
4514 }

4620{
4621 struct hresult_error
4622 {
4623 using from_abi_t = take_ownership_from_abi_t;
4624 static constexpr auto from_abi{ take_ownership_from_abi };
4625
4626 hresult_error() noexcept = default;
4627 hresult_error(hresult_error&&) = default;
4628 hresult_error& operator=(hresult_error&&) = default;
4629
4630 hresult_error(hresult_error const& other) noexcept :
4631 m_code(other.m_code),
4632 m_info(other.m_info)
4633 {
4634 }
4635
4636 hresult_error& operator=(hresult_error const& other) noexcept
4637 {
4638 m_code = other.m_code;
4639 m_info = other.m_info;
4640 return *this;
4641 }
4642
4643 explicit hresult_error(hresult const code) noexcept : m_code(verify_error(code))
4644 {
4645 originate(code, nullptr);
4646 }
4647
4648 hresult_error(hresult const code, param::hstring const& message) noexcept : m_code(verify_error(code))
4649 {
4650 originate(code, get_abi(message));
4651 }
4652
4653 hresult_error(hresult const code, take_ownership_from_abi_t) noexcept : m_code(verify_error(code))
4654 {
4655 com_ptr<impl::IErrorInfo> info;
4656 WINRT_IMPL_GetErrorInfo(0, info.put_void());
4657
4658 if ((m_info = info.try_as<impl::IRestrictedErrorInfo>()))
4659 {
4660 WINRT_VERIFY_(0, m_info->GetReference(m_debug_reference.put()));
4661
4662 if (auto info2 = m_info.try_as<impl::ILanguageExceptionErrorInfo2>())
4663 {
4664 WINRT_VERIFY_(0, info2->CapturePropagationContext(nullptr));
4665 }
4666 }
4667 else
4668 {
4669 impl::bstr_handle legacy;
4670
4671 if (info)
4672 {
4673 info->GetDescription(legacy.put());
4674 }
4675
4676 hstring message;
4677
4678 if (legacy)
4679 {
4680 message = impl::trim_hresult_message(legacy.get(), WINRT_IMPL_SysStringLen(legacy.get()));
4681 }
4682
4683 originate(code, get_abi(message));
4684 }
4685 }
4686
4687 hresult code() const noexcept
4688 {
4689 return m_code;
4690 }
4691
4692 hstring message() const noexcept
4693 {
4694 if (m_info)
4695 {
4696 int32_t code{};
4697 impl::bstr_handle fallback;
4698 impl::bstr_handle message;
4699 impl::bstr_handle unused;
4700
4701 if (0 == m_info->GetErrorDetails(fallback.put(), &code, message.put(), unused.put()))
4702 {
4703 if (code == m_code)
4704 {
4705 if (message)
4706 {
4707 return impl::trim_hresult_message(message.get(), WINRT_IMPL_SysStringLen(message.get()));
4708 }
4709 else
4710 {
4711 return impl::trim_hresult_message(fallback.get(), WINRT_IMPL_SysStringLen(fallback.get()));
4712 }
4713 }
4714 }
4715 }
4716
4717 return impl::message_from_hresult(m_code);
4718 }
4719
4720 template <typename To>
4721 auto try_as() const noexcept
4722 {
4723 return m_info.try_as<To>();
4724 }
4725
4726 hresult to_abi() const noexcept
4727 {
4728 if (m_info)
4729 {
4730 WINRT_IMPL_SetErrorInfo(0, m_info.try_as<impl::IErrorInfo>().get());
4731 }
4732
4733 return m_code;
4734 }
4735
4736 private:
4737
4738 static int32_t __stdcall fallback_RoOriginateLanguageException(int32_t error, void* message, void*) noexcept
4739 {
4740 com_ptr<impl::IErrorInfo> info(new (std::nothrow) impl::error_info_fallback(error, message), take_ownership_from_abi);
4741 WINRT_VERIFY_(0, WINRT_IMPL_SetErrorInfo(0, info.get()));
4742 return 1;
4743 }
4744
4745 void originate(hresult const code, void* message) noexcept
4746 {
4747 static int32_t(__stdcall* handler)(int32_t error, void* message, void* exception) noexcept;
4748 impl::load_runtime_function(L"combase.dll", "RoOriginateLanguageException", handler, fallback_RoOriginateLanguageException);
4749 WINRT_VERIFY(handler(code, message, nullptr));
4750
4751 com_ptr<impl::IErrorInfo> info;
4752 WINRT_VERIFY_(0, WINRT_IMPL_GetErrorInfo(0, info.put_void()));
4753 WINRT_VERIFY(info.try_as(m_info));
4754 }
4755
4756 static hresult verify_error(hresult const code) noexcept
4757 {
4758 WINRT_ASSERT(code < 0);
4759 return code;
4760 }

4766#endif

4769 uint32_t m_debug_magic{ 0xAABBCCDD };
4770 hresult m_code{ impl::error_fail };
4771 com_ptr<impl::IRestrictedErrorInfo> m_info;
4772

4776 };

4869 [[noreturn]] inline WINRT_IMPL_NOINLINE void throw_hresult(hresult const result)
4870 {
4871 if (winrt_throw_hresult_handler)
4872 {
4873 winrt_throw_hresult_handler(0, nullptr, nullptr, WINRT_IMPL_RETURNADDRESS(), result);
4874 }
4875
4876 if (result == impl::error_bad_alloc)
4877 {
4878 throw std::bad_alloc();
4879 }
4880
4881 if (result == impl::error_access_denied)
4882 {
4883 throw hresult_access_denied(take_ownership_from_abi);
4884 }
4885
4886 if (result == impl::error_wrong_thread)
4887 {
4888 throw hresult_wrong_thread(take_ownership_from_abi);
4889 }
4890
4891 if (result == impl::error_not_implemented)
4892 {
4893 throw hresult_not_implemented(take_ownership_from_abi);
4894 }
4895
4896 if (result == impl::error_invalid_argument)
4897 {
4898 throw hresult_invalid_argument(take_ownership_from_abi);
4899 }
4900
4901 if (result == impl::error_out_of_bounds)
4902 {
4903 throw hresult_out_of_bounds(take_ownership_from_abi);
4904 }
4905
4906 if (result == impl::error_no_interface)
4907 {
4908 throw hresult_no_interface(take_ownership_from_abi);
4909 }
4910
4911 if (result == impl::error_class_not_available)
4912 {
4913 throw hresult_class_not_available(take_ownership_from_abi);
4914 }
4915
4916 if (result == impl::error_class_not_registered)
4917 {
4918 throw hresult_class_not_registered(take_ownership_from_abi);
4919 }
4920
4921 if (result == impl::error_changed_state)
4922 {
4923 throw hresult_changed_state(take_ownership_from_abi);
4924 }
4925
4926 if (result == impl::error_illegal_method_call)
4927 {
4928 throw hresult_illegal_method_call(take_ownership_from_abi);
4929 }
4930
4931 if (result == impl::error_illegal_state_change)
4932 {
4933 throw hresult_illegal_state_change(take_ownership_from_abi);
4934 }
4935
4936 if (result == impl::error_illegal_delegate_assignment)
4937 {
4938 throw hresult_illegal_delegate_assignment(take_ownership_from_abi);
4939 }
4940
4941 if (result == impl::error_canceled)
4942 {
4943 throw hresult_canceled(take_ownership_from_abi);
4944 }
4945
4946 throw hresult_error(result, take_ownership_from_abi);
4947 }
4948
4949 inline WINRT_IMPL_NOINLINE hresult to_hresult() noexcept
4950 {
4951 if (winrt_to_hresult_handler)
4952 {
4953 return winrt_to_hresult_handler(WINRT_IMPL_RETURNADDRESS());
4954 }
4955
4956 try
4957 {
4958 throw;
4959 }
4960 catch (hresult_error const& e)
4961 {
4962 return e.to_abi();
4963 }
4964 catch (std::bad_alloc const&)
4965 {
4966 return impl::error_bad_alloc;
4967 }
4968 catch (std::out_of_range const& e)
4969 {
4970 return hresult_out_of_bounds(to_hstring(e.what())).to_abi();
4971 }
4972 catch (std::invalid_argument const& e)
4973 {
4974 return hresult_invalid_argument(to_hstring(e.what())).to_abi();
4975 }
4976 catch (std::exception const& e)
4977 {
4978 return hresult_error(impl::error_fail, to_hstring(e.what())).to_abi();
4979 }
4980 }
4981
4982 inline WINRT_IMPL_NOINLINE hstring to_message()
4983 {
4984 if (winrt_to_message_handler)
4985 {
4986 return winrt_to_message_handler(WINRT_IMPL_RETURNADDRESS());
4987 }
4988
4989 try
4990 {
4991 throw;
4992 }
4993 catch (hresult_error const& e)
4994 {
4995 return e.message();
4996 }
4997 catch (std::exception const& ex)
4998 {
4999 return to_hstring(ex.what());
5000 }
5001 catch (...)
5002 {
5003 abort();
5004 }
5005 }
5006
5007 [[noreturn]] inline void throw_last_error()
5008 {
5009 throw_hresult(impl::hresult_from_win32(WINRT_IMPL_GetLastError()));
5010 }
5011
5012 inline hresult check_hresult(hresult const result)
5013 {
5014 if (result < 0)
5015 {
5016 throw_hresult(result);
5017 }
5018 return result;
5019 }
5020
5021 template<typename T>
5022 void check_nt(T result)
5023 {
5024 if (result != 0)
5025 {
5026 throw_hresult(impl::hresult_from_nt(result));
5027 }
5028 }
5029
5030 template<typename T>
5031 void check_win32(T result)
5032 {
5033 if (result != 0)
5034 {
5035 throw_hresult(impl::hresult_from_win32(result));
5036 }
5037 }
5038
5039 template<typename T>
5040 void check_bool(T result)
5041 {
5042 if (!result)
5043 {
5044 winrt::throw_last_error();
5045 }
5046 }
5047
5048 template<typename T>
5049 T* check_pointer(T* pointer)
5050 {
5051 if (!pointer)
5052 {
5053 throw_last_error();
5054 }
5055
5056 return pointer;
5057 }
5058
5059 [[noreturn]] inline void terminate() noexcept
5060 {
5061 static void(__stdcall * handler)(int32_t) noexcept;
5062 impl::load_runtime_function(L"combase.dll", "RoFailFastWithErrorContext", handler, impl::fallback_RoFailFastWithErrorContext);
5063 handler(to_hresult());
5064 abort();
5065 }
5066}

5071 {
5072 if (result != impl::error_out_of_bounds && result != impl::error_fail && result != impl::error_file_not_found)
5073 {
5074 check_hresult(result);
5075 }
5076 return result;
5077 }

5084 inline int32_t make_marshaler(unknown_abi* outer, void** result) noexcept
5085 {
5086 struct marshaler final : IMarshal
5087 {
5088 marshaler(unknown_abi* object) noexcept
5089 {
5090 m_object.copy_from(object);
5091 }
5092
5093 int32_t __stdcall QueryInterface(guid const& id, void** object) noexcept final
5094 {
5095 if (is_guid_of<IMarshal>(id))
5096 {
5097 *object = static_cast<IMarshal*>(this);
5098 AddRef();
5099 return 0;
5100 }
5101
5102 return m_object->QueryInterface(id, object);
5103 }
5104
5105 uint32_t __stdcall AddRef() noexcept final
5106 {
5107 return ++m_references;
5108 }
5109
5110 uint32_t __stdcall Release() noexcept final
5111 {
5112 auto const remaining = --m_references;
5113
5114 if (remaining == 0)
5115 {
5116 delete this;
5117 }
5118
5119 return remaining;
5120 }
5121
5122 int32_t __stdcall GetUnmarshalClass(guid const& riid, void* pv, uint32_t dwDestContext, void* pvDestContext, uint32_t mshlflags, guid* pCid) noexcept final
5123 {
5124 if (m_marshaler)
5125 {
5126 return m_marshaler->GetUnmarshalClass(riid, pv, dwDestContext, pvDestContext, mshlflags, pCid);
5127 }
5128
5129 return error_bad_alloc;
5130 }
5131
5132 int32_t __stdcall GetMarshalSizeMax(guid const& riid, void* pv, uint32_t dwDestContext, void* pvDestContext, uint32_t mshlflags, uint32_t* pSize) noexcept final
5133 {
5134 if (m_marshaler)
5135 {
5136 return m_marshaler->GetMarshalSizeMax(riid, pv, dwDestContext, pvDestContext, mshlflags, pSize);
5137 }
5138
5139 return error_bad_alloc;
5140 }
5141
5142 int32_t __stdcall MarshalInterface(void* pStm, guid const& riid, void* pv, uint32_t dwDestContext, void* pvDestContext, uint32_t mshlflags) noexcept final
5143 {
5144 if (m_marshaler)
5145 {
5146 return m_marshaler->MarshalInterface(pStm, riid, pv, dwDestContext, pvDestContext, mshlflags);
5147 }
5148
5149 return error_bad_alloc;
5150 }
5151
5152 int32_t __stdcall UnmarshalInterface(void* pStm, guid const& riid, void** ppv) noexcept final
5153 {
5154 if (m_marshaler)
5155 {
5156 return m_marshaler->UnmarshalInterface(pStm, riid, ppv);
5157 }
5158
5159 *ppv = nullptr;
5160 return error_bad_alloc;
5161 }
5162
5163 int32_t __stdcall ReleaseMarshalData(void* pStm) noexcept final
5164 {
5165 if (m_marshaler)
5166 {
5167 return m_marshaler->ReleaseMarshalData(pStm);
5168 }
5169
5170 return error_bad_alloc;
5171 }
5172
5173 int32_t __stdcall DisconnectObject(uint32_t dwReserved) noexcept final
5174 {
5175 if (m_marshaler)
5176 {
5177 return m_marshaler->DisconnectObject(dwReserved);
5178 }
5179
5180 return error_bad_alloc;
5181 }
5182
5183 private:
5184
5185 static com_ptr<IMarshal> get_marshaler() noexcept
5186 {
5187 com_ptr<unknown_abi> unknown;
5188 WINRT_VERIFY_(0, WINRT_IMPL_CoCreateFreeThreadedMarshaler(nullptr, unknown.put_void()));
5189 return unknown ? unknown.try_as<IMarshal>() : nullptr;
5190 }
5191
5192 com_ptr<unknown_abi> m_object;
5193 com_ptr<IMarshal> m_marshaler{ get_marshaler() };
5194 atomic_ref_count m_references{ 1 };
5195 };
5196
5197 *result = new (std::nothrow) marshaler(outer);
5198 return *result ? error_ok : error_bad_alloc;
5199 }

5209 template <typename T, typename H>
5210 struct implements_delegate : abi_t<T>, H, update_module_lock
5211 {
5212 implements_delegate(H&& handler) : H(std::forward<H>(handler))
5213 {
5214 }
5215
5216 int32_t __stdcall QueryInterface(guid const& id, void** result) noexcept final
5217 {
5218 if (is_guid_of<T>(id) || is_guid_of<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown>(id) || is_guid_of<IAgileObject>(id))
5219 {
5220 *result = static_cast<abi_t<T>*>(this);
5221 AddRef();
5222 return 0;
5223 }
5224
5225 if (is_guid_of<IMarshal>(id))
5226 {
5227 return make_marshaler(this, result);
5228 }
5229
5230 *result = nullptr;
5231 return error_no_interface;
5232 }
5233
5234 uint32_t __stdcall AddRef() noexcept final
5235 {
5236 return ++m_references;
5237 }
5238
5239 uint32_t __stdcall Release() noexcept final
5240 {
5241 auto const remaining = --m_references;
5242
5243 if (remaining == 0)
5244 {
5245 delete static_cast<delegate<T, H>*>(this);
5246 }
5247
5248 return remaining;
5249 }
5250
5251 private:
5252
5253 atomic_ref_count m_references{ 1 };
5254 };
5255
5256 template <typename T, typename H>
5257 T make_delegate(H&& handler)
5258 {
5259 return { static_cast<void*>(static_cast<abi_t<T>*>(new delegate<T, H>(std::forward<H>(handler)))), take_ownership_from_abi };
5260 }
5261
5262 template <typename T>
5263 T make_agile_delegate(T const& delegate) noexcept
5264 {
5265 if constexpr (!has_category_v<T>)
5266 {
5267 return delegate;
5268 }
5269 else
5270 {
5271 if (delegate.template try_as<IAgileObject>())
5272 {
5273 return delegate;
5274 }
5275
5276 com_ptr<IAgileReference> ref;
5277 get_agile_reference(guid_of<T>(), get_abi(delegate), ref.put_void());
5278
5279 if (ref)
5280 {
5281 return [ref = std::move(ref)](auto&& ... args)
5282 {
5283 T delegate;
5284 ref->Resolve(guid_of<T>(), put_abi(delegate));
5285 return delegate(args...);
5286 };
5287 }
5288
5289 return delegate;
5290 }
5291 }
5292
5293 template <typename R, typename... Args>
5294 struct __declspec(novtable) variadic_delegate_abi : unknown_abi
5295 {
5296 virtual R invoke(Args const& ...) = 0;
5297 };
5298
5299 template <typename H, typename R, typename... Args>
5300 struct variadic_delegate final : variadic_delegate_abi<R, Args...>, H, update_module_lock
5301 {
5302 variadic_delegate(H&& handler) : H(std::forward<H>(handler))
5303 {
5304 }
5305
5306 R invoke(Args const& ... args) final
5307 {
5308 if constexpr (std::is_void_v<R>)
5309 {
5310 (*this)(args...);
5311 }
5312 else
5313 {
5314 return (*this)(args...);
5315 }
5316 }
5317
5318 int32_t __stdcall QueryInterface(guid const& id, void** result) noexcept final
5319 {
5320 if (is_guid_of<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown>(id) || is_guid_of<IAgileObject>(id))
5321 {
5322 *result = static_cast<unknown_abi*>(this);
5323 AddRef();
5324 return 0;
5325 }
5326
5327 *result = nullptr;
5328 return error_no_interface;
5329 }
5330
5331 uint32_t __stdcall AddRef() noexcept final
5332 {
5333 return ++m_references;
5334 }
5335
5336 uint32_t __stdcall Release() noexcept final
5337 {
5338 auto const remaining = --m_references;
5339
5340 if (remaining == 0)
5341 {
5342 delete this;
5343 }
5344
5345 return remaining;
5346 }
5347
5348 private:
5349
5350 atomic_ref_count m_references{ 1 };
5351 };
5352
5353 template <typename R, typename... Args>
5354 struct __declspec(empty_bases) delegate_base : Windows::Foundation::IUnknown
5355 {
5356 delegate_base(std::nullptr_t = nullptr) noexcept {}
5357 delegate_base(void* ptr, take_ownership_from_abi_t) noexcept : IUnknown(ptr, take_ownership_from_abi) {}
5358
5359 template <typename L>
5360 delegate_base(L handler) :
5361 delegate_base(make(std::forward<L>(handler)))
5362 {}
5363
5364 template <typename F> delegate_base(F* handler) :
5365 delegate_base([=](auto&& ... args) { return handler(args...); })
5366 {}
5367
5368 template <typename O, typename M> delegate_base(O* object, M method) :
5369 delegate_base([=](auto&& ... args) { return ((*object).*(method))(args...); })
5370 {}
5371
5372 template <typename O, typename M> delegate_base(com_ptr<O>&& object, M method) :
5373 delegate_base([o = std::move(object), method](auto&& ... args) { return ((*o).*(method))(args...); })
5374 {
5375 }
5376
5377 template <typename O, typename M> delegate_base(winrt::weak_ref<O>&& object, M method) :
5378 delegate_base([o = std::move(object), method](auto&& ... args) { if (auto s = o.get()) { ((*s).*(method))(args...); } })
5379 {
5380 }
5381
5382 auto operator()(Args const& ... args) const
5383 {
5384 return (*(variadic_delegate_abi<R, Args...> * *)this)->invoke(args...);
5385 }
5386
5387 private:
5388
5389 template <typename H>
5390 static delegate_base<R, Args...> make(H&& handler)
5391 {
5392 return { static_cast<void*>(new variadic_delegate<H, R, Args...>(std::forward<H>(handler))), take_ownership_from_abi };
5393 }
5394 };

5418 struct event_token
5419 {
5420 int64_t value{};
5421
5422 explicit operator bool() const noexcept
5423 {
5424 return value != 0;
5425 }
5426 };
5427
5428 inline bool operator==(event_token const& left, event_token const& right) noexcept
5429 {
5430 return left.value == right.value;
5431 }
5432
5433 struct auto_revoke_t {};
5434 inline constexpr auto_revoke_t auto_revoke{};
5435
5436 template <typename I>
5437 struct event_revoker
5438 {
5439 using method_type = int32_t(__stdcall impl::abi_t<I>::*)(winrt::event_token);
5440
5441 event_revoker() noexcept = default;
5442 event_revoker(event_revoker const&) = delete;
5443 event_revoker& operator=(event_revoker const&) = delete;
5444 event_revoker(event_revoker&&) noexcept = default;
5445
5446 event_revoker& operator=(event_revoker&& other) noexcept
5447 {
5448 if (this != &other)
5449 {
5450 revoke();
5451 m_object = std::move(other.m_object);
5452 m_method = other.m_method;
5453 m_token = other.m_token;
5454 }
5455
5456 return *this;
5457 }
5458
5459 template <typename U>
5460 event_revoker(U&& object, method_type method, event_token token) :
5461 m_object(std::forward<U>(object)),
5462 m_method(method),
5463 m_token(token)
5464 {}
5465
5466 ~event_revoker() noexcept
5467 {
5468 revoke();
5469 }
5470
5471 void revoke() noexcept
5472 {
5473 if (I object = std::exchange(m_object, {}).get())
5474 {
5475 ((*reinterpret_cast<impl::abi_t<I>**>(&object))->*(m_method))(m_token);
5476 }
5477 }
5478
5479 explicit operator bool() const noexcept
5480 {
5481 return m_object ? true : false;
5482 }
5483
5484 private:
5485
5486 weak_ref<I> m_object;
5487 method_type m_method{};
5488 event_token m_token{};
5489 };
5490
5491 template <typename I>
5492 struct factory_event_revoker
5493 {
5494 using method_type = int32_t(__stdcall impl::abi_t<I>::*)(winrt::event_token);
5495
5496 factory_event_revoker() noexcept = default;
5497 factory_event_revoker(factory_event_revoker const&) = delete;
5498 factory_event_revoker& operator=(factory_event_revoker const&) = delete;
5499 factory_event_revoker(factory_event_revoker&&) noexcept = default;
5500
5501 factory_event_revoker& operator=(factory_event_revoker&& other) noexcept
5502 {
5503 if (this != &other)
5504 {
5505 revoke();
5506 m_object = std::move(other.m_object);
5507 m_method = other.m_method;
5508 m_token = other.m_token;
5509 }
5510
5511 return *this;
5512 }
5513
5514 template <typename U>
5515 factory_event_revoker(U&& object, method_type method, event_token token) noexcept :
5516 m_object(std::forward<U>(object)),
5517 m_method(method),
5518 m_token(token)
5519 {}
5520
5521 ~factory_event_revoker() noexcept
5522 {
5523 revoke();
5524 }
5525
5526 void revoke() noexcept
5527 {
5528 if (auto object = std::exchange(m_object, {}))
5529 {
5530 ((*reinterpret_cast<impl::abi_t<I>**>(&object))->*(m_method))(m_token);
5531 }
5532 }
5533
5534 explicit operator bool() const noexcept
5535 {
5536 return m_object ? true : false;
5537 }
5538
5539 private:
5540
5541 I m_object;
5542 method_type m_method{};
5543 event_token m_token{};
5544 };
5545}

5676 template <typename T>
5677 struct event_array
5678 {
5679 using value_type = T;
5680 using reference = value_type&;
5681 using pointer = value_type*;
5682 using iterator = value_type*;
5683
5684 explicit event_array(uint32_t const count) noexcept : m_size(count)
5685 {
5686 std::uninitialized_fill_n(data(), count, value_type());
5687 }
5688
5689 unsigned long AddRef() noexcept
5690 {
5691 return ++m_references;
5692 }
5693
5694 unsigned long Release() noexcept
5695 {
5696 auto const remaining = --m_references;
5697
5698 if (remaining == 0)
5699 {
5700 this->~event_array();
5701 ::operator delete(static_cast<void*>(this));
5702 }
5703
5704 return remaining;
5705 }
5706
5707 reference back() noexcept
5708 {
5709 WINRT_ASSERT(m_size > 0);
5710 return*(data() + m_size - 1);
5711 }
5712
5713 iterator begin() noexcept
5714 {
5715 return data();
5716 }
5717
5718 iterator end() noexcept
5719 {
5720 return data() + m_size;
5721 }
5722
5723 uint32_t size() const noexcept
5724 {
5725 return m_size;
5726 }
5727
5728 ~event_array() noexcept
5729 {
5730 std::destroy(begin(), end());
5731 }
5732
5733 private:
5734
5735 pointer data() noexcept
5736 {
5737 return reinterpret_cast<pointer>(this + 1);
5738 }
5739
5740 atomic_ref_count m_references{ 1 };
5741 uint32_t m_size{ 0 };
5742 };
5743
5744 template <typename T>
5745 com_ptr<event_array<T>> make_event_array(uint32_t const capacity)
5746 {
5747 void* raw = ::operator new(sizeof(event_array<T>) + (sizeof(T)* capacity));
5748#pragma warning(suppress: 6386)
5749 return { new(raw) event_array<T>(capacity), take_ownership_from_abi };
5750 }
5751
5752 inline int32_t __stdcall fallback_RoTransformError(int32_t, int32_t, void*) noexcept
5753 {
5754 return 1;
5755 }
5756
5757 template <typename Delegate, typename... Arg>
5758 bool invoke(Delegate const& delegate, Arg const&... args) noexcept
5759 {
5760 try
5761 {
5762 delegate(args...);
5763 }
5764 catch (...)
5765 {
5766 int32_t const code = to_hresult();
5767
5768 static int32_t(__stdcall * handler)(int32_t, int32_t, void*) noexcept;
5769 impl::load_runtime_function(L"combase.dll", "RoTransformError", handler, fallback_RoTransformError);
5770 handler(code, 0, nullptr);
5771
5772 if (code == static_cast<int32_t>(0x80010108) || // RPC_E_DISCONNECTED
5773 code == static_cast<int32_t>(0x800706BA) || // HRESULT_FROM_WIN32(RPC_S_SERVER_UNAVAILABLE)
5774 code == static_cast<int32_t>(0x89020001)) // JSCRIPT_E_CANTEXECUTE
5775 {
5776 return false;
5777 }
5778 }
5779
5780 return true;
5781 }
5782}
5783
5784WINRT_EXPORT namespace winrt
5785{
5786 template <typename Delegate>
5787 struct event
5788 {
5789 using delegate_type = Delegate;
5790
5791 event() = default;
5792 event(event<Delegate> const&) = delete;
5793 event<Delegate>& operator =(event<Delegate> const&) = delete;
5794
5795 explicit operator bool() const noexcept
5796 {
5797 return m_targets != nullptr;
5798 }
5799
5800 event_token add(delegate_type const& delegate)
5801 {
5802 event_token token{};
5803
5804 // Extends life of old targets array to release delegates outside of lock.
5805 delegate_array temp_targets;
5806
5807 {
5808 slim_lock_guard const change_guard(m_change);
5809 delegate_array new_targets = impl::make_event_array<delegate_type>((!m_targets) ? 1 : m_targets->size() + 1);
5810
5811 if (m_targets)
5812 {
5813 std::copy_n(m_targets->begin(), m_targets->size(), new_targets->begin());
5814 }
5815
5816 new_targets->back() = impl::make_agile_delegate(delegate);
5817 token = get_token(new_targets->back());
5818
5819 slim_lock_guard const swap_guard(m_swap);
5820 temp_targets = std::exchange(m_targets, std::move(new_targets));
5821 }
5822
5823 return token;
5824 }
5825
5826 void remove(event_token const token)
5827 {
5828 // Extends life of old targets array to release delegates outside of lock.
5829 delegate_array temp_targets;
5830
5831 {
5832 slim_lock_guard const change_guard(m_change);
5833
5834 if (!m_targets)
5835 {
5836 return;
5837 }
5838
5839 uint32_t available_slots = m_targets->size() - 1;
5840 delegate_array new_targets;
5841 bool removed = false;
5842
5843 if (available_slots == 0)
5844 {
5845 if (get_token(*m_targets->begin()) == token)
5846 {
5847 removed = true;
5848 }
5849 }
5850 else
5851 {
5852 new_targets = impl::make_event_array<delegate_type>(available_slots);
5853 auto new_iterator = new_targets->begin();
5854
5855 for (delegate_type const& element : *m_targets)
5856 {
5857 if (!removed && token == get_token(element))
5858 {
5859 removed = true;
5860 continue;
5861 }
5862
5863 if (available_slots == 0)
5864 {
5865 WINRT_ASSERT(!removed);
5866 break;
5867 }
5868
5869 *new_iterator = element;
5870 ++new_iterator;
5871 --available_slots;
5872 }
5873 }
5874
5875 if (removed)
5876 {
5877 slim_lock_guard const swap_guard(m_swap);
5878 temp_targets = std::exchange(m_targets, std::move(new_targets));
5879 }
5880 }
5881 }
5882
5883 template<typename...Arg>
5884 void operator()(Arg const&... args)
5885 {
5886 delegate_array temp_targets;
5887
5888 {
5889 slim_lock_guard const swap_guard(m_swap);
5890 temp_targets = m_targets;
5891 }
5892
5893 if (temp_targets)
5894 {
5895 for (delegate_type const& element : *temp_targets)
5896 {
5897 if (!impl::invoke(element, args...))
5898 {
5899 remove(get_token(element));
5900 }
5901 }
5902 }
5903 }
5904
5905 private:
5906
5907 event_token get_token(delegate_type const& delegate) const noexcept
5908 {
5909 return event_token{ reinterpret_cast<int64_t>(WINRT_IMPL_EncodePointer(get_abi(delegate))) };
5910 }
5911
5912 using delegate_array = com_ptr<impl::event_array<delegate_type>>;
5913
5914 delegate_array m_targets;
5915 slim_mutex m_swap;
5916 slim_mutex m_change;
5917 };
5918}

5922 struct library_traits
5923 {
5924 using type = void*;
5925
5926 static void close(type value) noexcept
5927 {
5928 WINRT_IMPL_FreeLibrary(value);
5929 }
5930
5931 static constexpr type invalid() noexcept
5932 {
5933 return nullptr;
5934 }
5935 };
5936
5937 using library_handle = handle_type<library_traits>;
5938
5939 inline int32_t __stdcall fallback_RoGetActivationFactory(void*, guid const&, void** factory) noexcept
5940 {
5941 *factory = nullptr;
5942 return error_class_not_available;
5943 }
5944
5945
5946 template <bool isSameInterfaceAsIActivationFactory>
5947 WINRT_IMPL_NOINLINE hresult get_runtime_activation_factory_impl(param::hstring const& name, winrt::guid const& guid, void** result) noexcept
5948 {
5949 if (winrt_activation_handler)
5950 {
5951 return winrt_activation_handler(*(void**)(&name), guid, result);
5952 }
5953
5954 static int32_t(__stdcall * handler)(void* classId, winrt::guid const& iid, void** factory) noexcept;
5955 impl::load_runtime_function(L"combase.dll", "RoGetActivationFactory", handler, fallback_RoGetActivationFactory);
5956 hresult hr = handler(*(void**)(&name), guid, result);
5957
5958 if (hr == impl::error_not_initialized)
5959 {
5960 auto usage = reinterpret_cast<int32_t(__stdcall*)(void** cookie) noexcept>(WINRT_IMPL_GetProcAddress(WINRT_IMPL_LoadLibraryW(L"combase.dll"), "CoIncrementMTAUsage"));
5961
5962 if (!usage)
5963 {
5964 return hr;
5965 }
5966
5967 void* cookie;
5968 usage(&cookie);
5969 hr = handler(*(void**)(&name), guid, result);
5970 }
5971
5972 if (hr == 0)
5973 {
5974 return 0;
5975 }
5976
5977 com_ptr<IErrorInfo> error_info;
5978 WINRT_IMPL_GetErrorInfo(0, error_info.put_void());
5979
5980 std::wstring path{ static_cast<hstring const&>(name) };
5981 std::size_t count{};
5982
5983 while (std::wstring::npos != (count = path.rfind('.')))
5984 {
5985 path.resize(count);
5986 path += L".dll";
5987 library_handle library(WINRT_IMPL_LoadLibraryW(path.c_str()));
5988 path.resize(path.size() - 4);
5989
5990 if (!library)
5991 {
5992 continue;
5993 }
5994
5995 auto library_call = reinterpret_cast<int32_t(__stdcall*)(void* classId, void** factory)>(WINRT_IMPL_GetProcAddress(library.get(), "DllGetActivationFactory"));
5996
5997 if (!library_call)
5998 {
5999 continue;
6000 }
6001
6002 com_ptr<abi_t<Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory>> library_factory;
6003
6004 if (0 != library_call(*(void**)(&name), library_factory.put_void()))
6005 {
6006 continue;
6007 }
6008
6009 if constexpr (isSameInterfaceAsIActivationFactory)
6010 {
6011 *result = library_factory.detach();
6012 library.detach();
6013 return 0;
6014 }
6015 else if (0 == library_factory.as(guid, result))
6016 {
6017 library.detach();
6018 return 0;
6019 }
6020 }
6021
6022 WINRT_IMPL_SetErrorInfo(0, error_info.get());
6023 return hr;
6024 }
6025
6026 template <typename Interface>
6027 hresult get_runtime_activation_factory(param::hstring const& name, void** result) noexcept
6028 {
6029 return get_runtime_activation_factory_impl<std::is_same_v<Interface, Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory>>(name, guid_of<Interface>(), result);
6030 }
6031}

6036 impl::com_ref<Interface> get_activation_factory(param::hstring const& name)
6037 {
6038 void* result{};
6039 check_hresult(impl::get_runtime_activation_factory<Interface>(name, &result));
6040 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
6041 }
6042}

6058 {

6060 int32_t const result = *target;
6061 _ReadWriteBarrier();
6062 return result;
6063#elif defined _M_ARM || defined _M_ARM64
6064 int32_t const result = __iso_volatile_load32(reinterpret_cast<int32_t const volatile*>(target));
6065 WINRT_IMPL_INTERLOCKED_READ_MEMORY_BARRIER
6066 return result;
6067#else
6068#error Unsupported architecture
6069#endif
6070 }

6096 T* interlocked_read_pointer(T* const volatile* target) noexcept
6097 {
6098#ifdef _WIN64
6099 return (T*)interlocked_read_64((int64_t*)target);
6100#else
6101 return (T*)interlocked_read_32((int32_t*)target);
6102#endif

6106 inline constexpr uint32_t memory_allocation_alignment{ 16 };
6107#pragma warning(push)
6108#pragma warning(disable:4324) // structure was padded due to alignment specifier
6109 struct alignas(16) slist_entry
6110 {
6111 slist_entry* next;
6112 };
6113 union alignas(16) slist_header
6114 {
6115 struct
6116 {
6117 uint64_t reserved1;
6118 uint64_t reserved2;
6119 } reserved1;
6120 struct
6121 {
6122 uint64_t reserved1 : 16;
6123 uint64_t reserved2 : 48;
6124 uint64_t reserved3 : 4;
6125 uint64_t reserved4 : 60;
6126 } reserved2;
6127 };
6128#pragma warning(pop)
6129#else

6131 struct slist_entry
6132 {
6133 slist_entry* next;
6134 };
6135 union slist_header
6136 {
6137 uint64_t reserved1;
6138 struct
6139 {
6140 slist_entry reserved1;
6141 uint16_t reserved2;
6142 uint16_t reserved3;
6143 } reserved2;
