6147 struct factory_count_guard
6148 {
6149 factory_count_guard(factory_count_guard const&) = delete;
6150 factory_count_guard& operator=(factory_count_guard const&) = delete;
6151
6152 explicit factory_count_guard(size_t& count) noexcept : m_count(count)
6153 {
6154#ifdef _WIN64
6155 _InterlockedIncrement64((int64_t*)&m_count);
6156#else
6157 _InterlockedIncrement((long*)&m_count);
6158#endif
6159 }
6160
6161 ~factory_count_guard() noexcept
6162 {
6163#ifdef _WIN64
6164 _InterlockedDecrement64((int64_t*)&m_count);
6165#else
6166 _InterlockedDecrement((long*)&m_count);
6167#endif
6168 }
6169
6170 private:
6171
6172 size_t& m_count;
6173 };
6174
6175 struct factory_cache_entry_base
6176 {
6177 struct alignas(sizeof(void*) * 2) object_and_count
6178 {
6179 unknown_abi* object;
6180 size_t count;
6181 };
6182
6183 object_and_count m_value;
6184 alignas(memory_allocation_alignment) slist_entry m_next;
6185
6186 void clear() noexcept
6187 {
6188 unknown_abi* pointer_value = interlocked_read_pointer(&m_value.object);
6189
6190 if (pointer_value == nullptr)
6191 {
6192 return;
6193 }
6194
6195 object_and_count current_value{ pointer_value, 0 };
6196
6197#if defined _WIN64
6198 if (1 == _InterlockedCompareExchange128((int64_t*)this, 0, 0, (int64_t*)&current_value))
6199 {
6200 pointer_value->Release();
6201 }
6202#else
6203 int64_t const result = _InterlockedCompareExchange64((int64_t*)this, 0, *(int64_t*)&current_value);
6204
6205 if (result == *(int64_t*)&current_value)
6206 {
6207 pointer_value->Release();
6208 }
6209#endif
6210 }
6211 };
6212
6213 static_assert(std::is_standard_layout_v<factory_cache_entry_base>);
6214
6215#if !defined _M_IX86 && !defined _M_X64 && !defined _M_ARM && !defined _M_ARM64
6216#error Unsupported architecture: verify that zero-initialization of SLIST_HEADER is still safe
6217#endif
6218
6219 struct factory_cache
6220 {
6221 factory_cache(factory_cache const&) = delete;
6222 factory_cache& operator=(factory_cache const&) = delete;
6223 factory_cache() noexcept = default;
6224
6225 void add(factory_cache_entry_base* const entry) noexcept
6226 {
6227 WINRT_ASSERT(entry);
6228 WINRT_IMPL_InterlockedPushEntrySList(&m_list, &entry->m_next);
6229 }
6230
6231 void clear() noexcept
6232 {
6233 slist_entry* entry = static_cast<slist_entry*>(WINRT_IMPL_InterlockedFlushSList(&m_list));
6234
6235 while (entry != nullptr)
6236 {
6237 // entry->next must be read before entry->clear() is called since the InterlockedCompareExchange
6238 // inside clear() will allow another thread to add the entry back to the cache.
6239 slist_entry* next = entry->next;
6240 reinterpret_cast<factory_cache_entry_base*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(entry) - offsetof(factory_cache_entry_base, m_next))->clear();
6241 entry = next;
6242 }
6243 }
6244
6245 private:
6246
6247 alignas(memory_allocation_alignment) slist_header m_list;
6248 };
6249
6250 inline factory_cache& get_factory_cache() noexcept
6251 {
6252 static factory_cache cache;
6253 return cache;
6254 }
6255
6256 template <typename Class, typename Interface>
6257 struct factory_cache_entry : factory_cache_entry_base
6258 {
6259 template <typename F>
6260 WINRT_IMPL_NOINLINE auto call(F&& callback)
6261 {
6262#ifdef WINRT_DIAGNOSTICS
6263 get_diagnostics_info().add_factory<Class>();
6264#endif
6265
6266 auto object = get_activation_factory<Interface>(name_of<Class>());
6267
6268 if (!object.template try_as<IAgileObject>())
6269 {
6270#ifdef WINRT_DIAGNOSTICS
6271 get_diagnostics_info().non_agile_factory<Class>();
6272#endif
6273
6274 return callback(object);
6275 }
6276
6277 {
6278 factory_count_guard const guard(m_value.count);
6279
6280 if (nullptr == _InterlockedCompareExchangePointer(reinterpret_cast<void**>(&m_value.object), *reinterpret_cast<void**>(&object), nullptr))
6281 {
6282 *reinterpret_cast<void**>(&object) = nullptr;
6283 get_factory_cache().add(this);
6284 }
6285
6286 return callback(*reinterpret_cast<com_ref<Interface> const*>(&m_value.object));
6287 }
6288 }
6289 };
6290
6291 template <typename Class, typename Interface>
6292 factory_cache_entry<Class, Interface> factory_cache_entry_v{};
6293
6294 template <typename Class, typename Interface = Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory, typename F>
6295 auto call_factory(F&& callback)
6296 {
6297 auto& factory = factory_cache_entry_v<Class, Interface>;
6298
6299 {
6300 factory_count_guard const guard(factory.m_value.count);
6301
6302 if (factory.m_value.object)
6303 {
6304 return callback(*reinterpret_cast<com_ref<Interface> const*>(&factory.m_value.object));
6305 }
6306 }
6307
6308 return factory.call(callback);
6309 }
6310
6311 template <typename CastType, typename Class, typename Interface = Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory, typename F>
6312 auto call_factory_cast(F&& callback)
6313 {
6314 auto& factory = factory_cache_entry_v<Class, Interface>;
6315
6316 {
6317 factory_count_guard const guard(factory.m_value.count);
6318
6319 if (factory.m_value.object)
6320 {
6321 return callback(*reinterpret_cast<com_ref<Interface> const*>(&factory.m_value.object));
6322 }
6323 }
6324
6325 return factory.call(static_cast<CastType>(callback));
6326 }
6327
6328 template <typename Interface = Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory>
6329 com_ref<Interface> try_get_activation_factory(param::hstring const& name, hresult_error* exception = nullptr) noexcept
6330 {
6331 void* result{};
6332 hresult const hr = get_runtime_activation_factory<Interface>(name, &result);
6333
6334 if (hr < 0)
6335 {
6336 // Ensure that the IRestrictedErrorInfo is not left on the thread.
6337 hresult_error local_exception{ hr, take_ownership_from_abi };
6338
6339 if (exception)
6340 {
6341 // Optionally transfer ownership to the caller.
6342 *exception = std::move(local_exception);
6343 }
6344 }
6345
6346 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
6347 }
6348
6349 template <typename D> struct produce<D, Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory> : produce_base<D, Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory>
6350 {
6351 int32_t __stdcall ActivateInstance(void** instance) noexcept final try
6352 {
6353 *instance = nullptr;
6354 typename D::abi_guard guard(this->shim());
6355 *instance = detach_abi(this->shim().ActivateInstance());
6356 return 0;
6357 }
6358 catch (...) { return to_hresult(); }
6359 };
6360}

6371 {

6373

6377 }

6384
6385 template <typename Class, typename Interface = Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory>
6386 auto get_activation_factory()
6387 {
6388 // Normally, the callback avoids having to return a ref-counted object and the resulting AddRef/Release bump.
6389 // In this case we do want a unique reference, so we use the lambda to return one and thus produce an
6390 // AddRef'd object that is returned to the caller.
6391 return impl::call_factory<Class, Interface>([](auto&& factory)
6392 {
6393 return factory;
6394 });
6395 }
6396

6398 auto try_get_activation_factory() noexcept
6399 {
6400 return impl::try_get_activation_factory<Interface>(name_of<Class>());
6401 }

6407 }

6725 template <typename...> struct interface_list;
6726
6727 template <>
6728 struct interface_list<>
6729 {
6730 template <typename T, typename Predicate>
6731 static constexpr void* find(const T*, const Predicate&) noexcept
6732 {
6733 return nullptr;
6734 }
6735 };
6736
6737 template <typename First, typename ... Rest>
6738 struct interface_list<First, Rest...>
6739 {
6740 template <typename T, typename Predicate>
6741 static constexpr void* find(const T* obj, const Predicate& pred) noexcept
6742 {
6743 if (pred.template test<First>())
6744 {
6745 return to_abi<First>(obj);
6746 }
6747 return interface_list<Rest...>::find(obj, pred);
6748 }
6749 using first_interface = First;
6750 };
6751
6752 template <typename, typename> struct interface_list_append_impl;
6753
6754 template <typename... T, typename... U>
6755 struct interface_list_append_impl<interface_list<T...>, interface_list<U...>>
6756 {
6757 using type = interface_list<T..., U...>;
6758 };
6759
6760 template <template <typename> class, typename...>
6761 struct filter_impl;
6762
6763 template <template <typename> class Predicate, typename... T>
6764 using filter = typename filter_impl<Predicate, unwrap_implements_t<T>...>::type;
6765
6766 template <template <typename> class Predicate>
6767 struct filter_impl<Predicate>
6768 {
6769 using type = interface_list<>;
6770 };
6771
6772 template <template <typename> class Predicate, typename T, typename... Rest>
6773 struct filter_impl<Predicate, T, Rest...>
6774 {
6775 using type = typename interface_list_append_impl<
6776 std::conditional_t<
6777 Predicate<T>::value,
6778 interface_list<winrt::impl::uncloak<T>>,
6779 interface_list<>
6780 >,
6781 typename filter_impl<Predicate, Rest...>::type
6782 >::type;
6783 };
6784
6785 template <template <typename> class Predicate, typename ... T, typename ... Rest>
6786 struct filter_impl<Predicate, interface_list<T...>, Rest...>
6787 {
6788 using type = typename interface_list_append_impl<
6789 filter<Predicate, T...>,
6790 filter<Predicate, Rest...>
6791 >::type;
6792 };
6793
6794 template <template <typename> class Predicate, typename D, typename ... I, typename ... Rest>
6795 struct filter_impl<Predicate, winrt::implements<D, I...>, Rest...>
6796 {
6797 using type = typename interface_list_append_impl<
6798 filter<Predicate, I...>,
6799 filter<Predicate, Rest...>
6800 >::type;
6801 };

7013 struct weak_source final : IWeakReferenceSource, module_lock_updater<UseModuleLock>
7014 {
7015 weak_ref<Agile, UseModuleLock>* that() noexcept
7016 {
7017 return static_cast<weak_ref<Agile, UseModuleLock>*>(reinterpret_cast<weak_source_producer<Agile, UseModuleLock>*>(this));
7018 }
7019
7020 int32_t __stdcall QueryInterface(guid const& id, void** object) noexcept final
7021 {
7022 if (is_guid_of<IWeakReferenceSource>(id))
7023 {
7024 *object = static_cast<IWeakReferenceSource*>(this);
7025 that()->increment_strong();
7026 return 0;
7027 }
7028
7029 return that()->m_object->QueryInterface(id, object);
7030 }
7031
7032 uint32_t __stdcall AddRef() noexcept final
7033 {
7034 return that()->increment_strong();
7035 }
7036
7037 uint32_t __stdcall Release() noexcept final
7038 {
7039 return that()->m_object->Release();
7040 }
7041
7042 int32_t __stdcall GetWeakReference(IWeakReference** weakReference) noexcept final
7043 {
7044 *weakReference = that();
7045 that()->AddRef();
7046 return 0;
7047 }
7048 };
7049
7050 template <bool Agile, bool UseModuleLock>
7051 struct weak_source_producer
7052 {
7053 protected:
7054 weak_source<Agile, UseModuleLock> m_source;
7055 };
7056
7057 template <bool Agile, bool UseModuleLock>
7058 struct weak_ref final : IWeakReference, weak_source_producer<Agile, UseModuleLock>
7059 {
7060 weak_ref(unknown_abi* object, uint32_t const strong) noexcept :
7061 m_object(object),
7062 m_strong(strong)
7063 {
7064 WINRT_ASSERT(object);
7065 }
7066
7067 int32_t __stdcall QueryInterface(guid const& id, void** object) noexcept final
7068 {
7069 if (is_guid_of<IWeakReference>(id) || is_guid_of<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown>(id))
7070 {
7071 *object = static_cast<IWeakReference*>(this);
7072 AddRef();
7073 return 0;
7074 }
7075
7076 if constexpr (Agile)
7077 {
7078 if (is_guid_of<IAgileObject>(id))
7079 {
7080 *object = static_cast<unknown_abi*>(this);
7081 AddRef();
7082 return 0;
7083 }
7084
7085 if (is_guid_of<IMarshal>(id))
7086 {
7087 return make_marshaler(this, object);
7088 }
7089 }
7090
7091 *object = nullptr;
7092 return error_no_interface;
7093 }
7094
7095 uint32_t __stdcall AddRef() noexcept final
7096 {
7097 return 1 + m_weak.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_relaxed);
7098 }
7099
7100 uint32_t __stdcall Release() noexcept final
7101 {
7102 uint32_t const target = m_weak.fetch_sub(1, std::memory_order_relaxed) - 1;
7103
7104 if (target == 0)
7105 {
7106 delete this;
7107 }
7108
7109 return target;
7110 }
7111
7112 int32_t __stdcall Resolve(guid const& id, void** objectReference) noexcept final
7113 {
7114 uint32_t target = m_strong.load(std::memory_order_relaxed);
7115
7116 while (true)
7117 {
7118 if (target == 0)
7119 {
7120 *objectReference = nullptr;
7121 return 0;
7122 }
7123
7124 if (m_strong.compare_exchange_weak(target, target + 1, std::memory_order_acquire, std::memory_order_relaxed))
7125 {
7126 int32_t hr = m_object->QueryInterface(id, objectReference);
7127 m_strong.fetch_sub(1, std::memory_order_relaxed);
7128 return hr;
7129 }
7130 }
7131 }
7132
7133 void set_strong(uint32_t const count) noexcept
7134 {
7135 m_strong = count;
7136 }
7137
7138 uint32_t increment_strong() noexcept
7139 {
7140 return 1 + m_strong.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_relaxed);
7141 }
7142
7143 uint32_t decrement_strong() noexcept
7144 {
7145 uint32_t const target = m_strong.fetch_sub(1, std::memory_order_release) - 1;
7146
7147 if (target == 0)
7148 {
7149 Release();
7150 }
7151
7152 return target;
7153 }
7154
7155 IWeakReferenceSource* get_source() noexcept
7156 {
7157 increment_strong();
7158 return &this->m_source;
7159 }
7160
7161 private:
7162 template <bool T, bool U>
7163 friend struct weak_source;
7164
7165 static_assert(sizeof(weak_source_producer<Agile, UseModuleLock>) == sizeof(weak_source<Agile, UseModuleLock>));
7166
7167 unknown_abi* m_object{};
7168 std::atomic<uint32_t> m_strong{ 1 };
7169 std::atomic<uint32_t> m_weak{ 1 };
7170 };

7223 template <typename D, typename... I>
7224 struct __declspec(novtable) root_implements
7225 : root_implements_composing_outer<std::disjunction_v<std::is_same<composing, I>...>>
7226 , root_implements_composable_inner<D, std::disjunction_v<std::is_same<composable, I>...>>
7227 , module_lock_updater<!std::disjunction_v<std::is_same<no_module_lock, I>...>>

7230 using root_implements_type = root_implements;

7232 int32_t __stdcall QueryInterface(guid const& id, void** object) noexcept
7233 {

7235 {
7236 return this->outer()->QueryInterface(id, object);
7237 }
7238

7240
7241 if (result == error_no_interface && this->m_inner)
7242 {
7243 result = static_cast<unknown_abi*>(get_abi(this->m_inner))->QueryInterface(id, object);
7244 }
7245
7246 return result;
7247 }

7309 subtract_reference();

7325 {

7327 }

7335 {

7341
7342 uint32_t __stdcall NonDelegatingAddRef() noexcept
7343 {
7344 if constexpr (is_weak_ref_source::value)
7345 {
7346 uintptr_t count_or_pointer = m_references.load(std::memory_order_relaxed);
7347
7348 while (true)
7349 {
7350 if (is_weak_ref(count_or_pointer))
7351 {
7352 return decode_weak_ref(count_or_pointer)->increment_strong();
7353 }
7354
7355 uintptr_t const target = count_or_pointer + 1;
7356
7357 if (m_references.compare_exchange_weak(count_or_pointer, target, std::memory_order_relaxed))
7358 {
7359 return static_cast<uint32_t>(target);
7360 }
7361 }
7362 }
7363 else
7364 {
7365 return 1 + m_references.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_relaxed);
7366 }
7367 }
7368
7369 uint32_t __stdcall NonDelegatingRelease() noexcept
7370 {
7371 uint32_t const target = subtract_reference();
7372
7373 if (target == 0)
7374 {
7375 // If a weak reference was previously created, the m_references value will not be stable value (won't be zero).
7376 // This ensures destruction has a stable value during destruction.
7377 m_references = 1;
7378
7379 if constexpr (has_final_release::value)
7380 {
7381 D::final_release(std::unique_ptr<D>(static_cast<D*>(this)));
7382 }
7383 else
7384 {
7385 delete this;
7386 }
7387 }
7388
7389 return target;
7390 }
7391
7392 int32_t __stdcall NonDelegatingQueryInterface(const guid& id, void** object) noexcept
7393 {
7394 if (is_guid_of<Windows::Foundation::IInspectable>(id) || is_guid_of<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown>(id))
7395 {
7396 auto result = to_abi<INonDelegatingInspectable>(this);
7397 NonDelegatingAddRef();
7398 *object = result;
7399 return 0;
7400 }
7401
7402 int32_t result = query_interface(id, object);
7403
7404 if (result == error_no_interface && this->m_inner)
7405 {
7406 result = static_cast<unknown_abi*>(get_abi(this->m_inner))->QueryInterface(id, object);
7407 }
7408
7409 return result;
7410 }
7411
7412 int32_t __stdcall NonDelegatingGetIids(uint32_t* count, guid** array) noexcept
7413 {
7414 const auto& local_iids = static_cast<D*>(this)->get_local_iids();
7415 const uint32_t& local_count = local_iids.first;
7416 if constexpr (root_implements_type::is_composing)
7417 {
7418 if (local_count > 0)
7419 {
7420 const com_array<guid>& inner_iids = get_interfaces(root_implements_type::m_inner);
7421 *count = local_count + inner_iids.size();
7422 *array = static_cast<guid*>(WINRT_IMPL_CoTaskMemAlloc(sizeof(guid)*(*count)));
7423 if (*array == nullptr)
7424 {
7425 return error_bad_alloc;
7426 }
7427 *array = std::copy(local_iids.second, local_iids.second + local_count, *array);
7428 std::copy(inner_iids.cbegin(), inner_iids.cend(), *array);
7429 }
7430 else
7431 {
7432 return static_cast<inspectable_abi*>(get_abi(root_implements_type::m_inner))->GetIids(count, array);
7433 }
7434 }
7435 else
7436 {
7437 if (local_count > 0)
7438 {
7439 *count = local_count;
7440 *array = static_cast<guid*>(WINRT_IMPL_CoTaskMemAlloc(sizeof(guid)*(*count)));
7441 if (*array == nullptr)
7442 {
7443 return error_bad_alloc;
7444 }
7445 std::copy(local_iids.second, local_iids.second + local_count, *array);
7446 }
7447 else
7448 {
7449 *count = 0;
7450 *array = nullptr;
7451 }
7452 }
7453 return 0;
7454 }
7455
7456 int32_t __stdcall NonDelegatingGetRuntimeClassName(void** name) noexcept try
7457 {
7458 *name = detach_abi(static_cast<D*>(this)->GetRuntimeClassName());
7459 return 0;
7460 }
7461 catch (...) { return to_hresult(); }
7462
7463 int32_t __stdcall NonDelegatingGetTrustLevel(Windows::Foundation::TrustLevel* trustLevel) noexcept try
7464 {
7465 *trustLevel = static_cast<D*>(this)->GetTrustLevel();
7466 return 0;
7467 }
7468 catch (...) { return to_hresult(); }
7469
7470 uint32_t subtract_reference() noexcept
7471 {
7472 if constexpr (is_weak_ref_source::value)
7473 {
7474 uintptr_t count_or_pointer = m_references.load(std::memory_order_relaxed);
7475
7476 while (true)
7477 {
7478 if (is_weak_ref(count_or_pointer))
7479 {
7480 return decode_weak_ref(count_or_pointer)->decrement_strong();
7481 }
7482
7483 uintptr_t const target = count_or_pointer - 1;
7484
7485 if (m_references.compare_exchange_weak(count_or_pointer, target, std::memory_order_release, std::memory_order_relaxed))
7486 {
7487 return static_cast<uint32_t>(target);
7488 }
7489 }
7490 }
7491 else
7492 {
7493 return m_references.fetch_sub(1, std::memory_order_release) - 1;
7494 }
7495 }
7496
7497 template <typename T>
7498 winrt::weak_ref<T> get_weak()
7499 {
7500 impl::IWeakReferenceSource* weak_ref = make_weak_ref();
7501 if (!weak_ref)
7502 {
7503 throw std::bad_alloc{};
7504 }
7505 com_ptr<impl::IWeakReferenceSource> source;
7506 attach_abi(source, weak_ref);
7507
7508 winrt::weak_ref<T> result;
7509 check_hresult(source->GetWeakReference(result.put()));
7510 return result;
7511 }
7512
7513 virtual Windows::Foundation::TrustLevel GetTrustLevel() const noexcept
7514 {
7515 return Windows::Foundation::TrustLevel::BaseTrust;
7516 }
7517
7518 private:
7519
7520 class has_final_release
7521 {
7522 template <typename U, typename = decltype(std::declval<U>().final_release(0))> static constexpr bool get_value(int) { return true; }
7523 template <typename> static constexpr bool get_value(...) { return false; }
7524
7525 public:
7526
7527 static constexpr bool value = get_value<D>(0);
7528 };
7529
7530 using is_agile = std::negation<std::disjunction<std::is_same<non_agile, I>...>>;
7531 using is_inspectable = std::disjunction<std::is_base_of<Windows::Foundation::IInspectable, I>...>;
7532 using is_weak_ref_source = std::conjunction<is_inspectable, std::negation<std::disjunction<std::is_same<no_weak_ref, I>...>>>;
7533 using use_module_lock = std::negation<std::disjunction<std::is_same<no_module_lock, I>...>>;
7534 using weak_ref_t = impl::weak_ref<is_agile::value, use_module_lock::value>;
7535
7536 std::atomic<std::conditional_t<is_weak_ref_source::value, uintptr_t, uint32_t>> m_references{ 1 };
7537
7538 int32_t query_interface(guid const& id, void** object) noexcept
7539 {
7540 *object = static_cast<D*>(this)->find_interface(id);
7541
7542 if (*object != nullptr)
7543 {
7544 AddRef();
7545 return 0;
7546 }
7547
7548 if constexpr (is_agile::value)
7549 {
7550 if (is_guid_of<IAgileObject>(id))
7551 {
7552 *object = get_unknown();
7553 AddRef();
7554 return 0;
7555 }
7556
7557 if (is_guid_of<IMarshal>(id))
7558 {
7559 return make_marshaler(get_unknown(), object);
7560 }
7561 }
7562
7563 if constexpr (is_inspectable::value)
7564 {
7565 if (is_guid_of<Windows::Foundation::IInspectable>(id))
7566 {
7567 *object = find_inspectable();
7568 AddRef();
7569 return 0;
7570 }
7571 }
7572
7573 if (is_guid_of<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown>(id))
7574 {
7575 *object = get_unknown();
7576 AddRef();
7577 return 0;
7578 }
7579
7580 if constexpr (is_weak_ref_source::value)
7581 {
7582 if (is_guid_of<impl::IWeakReferenceSource>(id))
7583 {
7584 *object = make_weak_ref();
7585 return *object ? error_ok : error_bad_alloc;
7586 }
7587 }
7588
7589 return query_interface_tearoff(id, object);
7590 }
7591
7592 impl::IWeakReferenceSource* make_weak_ref() noexcept
7593 {
7594 static_assert(is_weak_ref_source::value, "This is only for weak ref support.");
7595 uintptr_t count_or_pointer = m_references.load(std::memory_order_relaxed);
7596
7597 if (is_weak_ref(count_or_pointer))
7598 {
7599 return decode_weak_ref(count_or_pointer)->get_source();
7600 }
7601
7602 com_ptr<weak_ref_t> weak_ref;
7603 *weak_ref.put() = new (std::nothrow) weak_ref_t(get_unknown(), static_cast<uint32_t>(count_or_pointer));
7604
7605 if (!weak_ref)
7606 {
7607 return nullptr;
7608 }
7609
7610 uintptr_t const encoding = encode_weak_ref(weak_ref.get());
7611
7612 for (;;)
7613 {
7614 if (m_references.compare_exchange_weak(count_or_pointer, encoding, std::memory_order_acq_rel, std::memory_order_relaxed))
7615 {
7616 impl::IWeakReferenceSource* result = weak_ref->get_source();
7617 detach_abi(weak_ref);
7618 return result;
7619 }
7620
7621 if (is_weak_ref(count_or_pointer))
7622 {
7623 return decode_weak_ref(count_or_pointer)->get_source();
7624 }
7625
7626 weak_ref->set_strong(static_cast<uint32_t>(count_or_pointer));
7627 }
7628 }
7629
7630 static bool is_weak_ref(intptr_t const value) noexcept
7631 {
7632 static_assert(is_weak_ref_source::value, "This is only for weak ref support.");
7633 return value < 0;
7634 }
7635
7636 static weak_ref_t* decode_weak_ref(uintptr_t const value) noexcept
7637 {
7638 static_assert(is_weak_ref_source::value, "This is only for weak ref support.");
7639 return reinterpret_cast<weak_ref_t*>(value << 1);
7640 }
7641
7642 static uintptr_t encode_weak_ref(weak_ref_t* value) noexcept
7643 {
7644 static_assert(is_weak_ref_source::value, "This is only for weak ref support.");
7645 constexpr uintptr_t pointer_flag = static_cast<uintptr_t>(1) << ((sizeof(uintptr_t) * 8) - 1);
7646 WINRT_ASSERT((reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(value) & 1) == 0);
7647 return (reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(value) >> 1) | pointer_flag;
7648 }
7649
7650 virtual unknown_abi* get_unknown() const noexcept = 0;
7651 virtual std::pair<uint32_t, const guid*> get_local_iids() const noexcept = 0;
7652 virtual hstring GetRuntimeClassName() const = 0;
7653 virtual void* find_interface(guid const&) const noexcept = 0;
7654 virtual inspectable_abi* find_inspectable() const noexcept = 0;
7655
7656 template <typename, typename, typename>
7657 friend struct impl::produce_base;
7658
7659 template <typename, typename>
7660 friend struct impl::produce;
7661 };

7663#if defined(WINRT_NO_MAKE_DETECTION)
7664 template <typename T>
7665 using heap_implements = T;
7666#else
7667 template <typename T>
7668 struct heap_implements final : T
7669 {
7670 using T::T;
7671
7672#if defined(_DEBUG)
7673 void use_make_function_to_create_this_object() final
7674 {
7675 }
7676#endif
7677 };
7678#endif
7679
7680 inline com_ptr<IStaticLifetimeCollection> get_static_lifetime_map()
7681 {
7682 auto const lifetime_factory = get_activation_factory<impl::IStaticLifetime>(L"Windows.ApplicationModel.Core.CoreApplication");
7683 Windows::Foundation::IUnknown collection;
7684 check_hresult(lifetime_factory->GetCollection(put_abi(collection)));
7685 return collection.as<IStaticLifetimeCollection>();
7686 }
7687
7688 template <typename D>
7689 auto make_factory() -> typename impl::implements_default_interface<D>::type
7690 {
7691 using result_type = typename impl::implements_default_interface<D>::type;
7692
7693 if constexpr (!has_static_lifetime_v<D>)
7694 {
7695 return { to_abi<result_type>(new heap_implements<D>), take_ownership_from_abi };
7696 }
7697 else
7698 {
7699 auto const map = get_static_lifetime_map();
7700 param::hstring const name{ name_of<typename D::instance_type>() };
7701 void* result{};
7702 map->Lookup(get_abi(name), &result);
7703
7704 if (result)
7705 {
7706 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
7707 }
7708
7709 result_type object{ to_abi<result_type>(new heap_implements<D>), take_ownership_from_abi };
7710
7711 static slim_mutex lock;
7712 slim_lock_guard const guard{ lock };
7713 map->Lookup(get_abi(name), &result);
7714
7715 if (result)
7716 {
7717 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
7718 }
7719 else
7720 {
7721 bool found;
7722 check_hresult(map->Insert(get_abi(name), get_abi(object), &found));
7723 return object;
7724 }
7725 }
7726 }
7727
7728 template <typename T>
7729 auto detach_from(T&& object) noexcept
7730 {
7731 return detach_abi(std::forward<T>(object));
7732 }
7733}
7734
7735WINRT_EXPORT namespace winrt
7736{
7737 template <typename D, typename... Args>
7738 auto make(Args&&... args)
7739 {
7740#if !defined(WINRT_NO_MAKE_DETECTION)
7741 // Note: https://aka.ms/cppwinrt/detect_direct_allocations
7742 static_assert(std::is_destructible_v<D>, "C++/WinRT implementation types must have a public destructor");
7743 static_assert(!std::is_final_v<D>, "C++/WinRT implementation types must not be final");
7744#endif
7745
7746 using I = typename impl::implements_default_interface<D>::type;
7747
7748 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<I, Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory>)
7749 {
7750 static_assert(sizeof...(args) == 0);
7751 return impl::make_factory<D>();
7752 }
7753 else if constexpr (impl::has_composable<D>::value)
7754 {
7755 impl::com_ref<I> result{ to_abi<I>(new impl::heap_implements<D>(std::forward<Args>(args)...)), take_ownership_from_abi };
7756 return result.template as<typename D::composable>();
7757 }
7758 else if constexpr (impl::has_class_type<D>::value)
7759 {
7760 static_assert(std::is_same_v<I, default_interface<typename D::class_type>>);
7761 return typename D::class_type{ to_abi<I>(new impl::heap_implements<D>(std::forward<Args>(args)...)), take_ownership_from_abi };
7762 }
7763 else
7764 {
7765 return impl::com_ref<I>{ to_abi<I>(new impl::heap_implements<D>(std::forward<Args>(args)...)), take_ownership_from_abi };
7766 }
7767 }
7768
7769 template <typename D, typename... Args>
7770 com_ptr<D> make_self(Args&&... args)
7771 {
7772#if !defined(WINRT_NO_MAKE_DETECTION)
7773 // Note: https://aka.ms/cppwinrt/detect_direct_allocations
7774 static_assert(std::is_destructible_v<D>, "C++/WinRT implementation types must have a public destructor");
7775 static_assert(!std::is_final_v<D>, "C++/WinRT implementation types must not be final");
7776#endif
7777 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<typename impl::implements_default_interface<D>::type, Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory>)
7778 {
7779 static_assert(sizeof...(args) == 0);
7780 auto temp = impl::make_factory<D>();
7781 void* result = get_self<D>(temp);
7782 detach_abi(temp);
7783 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
7784 }
7785 else
7786 {
7787 return { new impl::heap_implements<D>(std::forward<Args>(args)...), take_ownership_from_abi };
7788 }
7789 }
7790
7791 template <typename... FactoryClasses>
7792 inline void clear_factory_static_lifetime()
7793 {
7794 auto unregister = [map = impl::get_static_lifetime_map()](param::hstring name)
7795 {
7796 map->Remove(get_abi(name));
7797 };
7798 ((unregister(name_of<typename FactoryClasses::instance_type>())), ...);
7799 }
7800
7801 template <typename D, typename... I>
7802 struct implements : impl::producers<D, I...>, impl::base_implements<D, I...>::type
7803 {
7804 protected:
7805
7806 using base_type = typename impl::base_implements<D, I...>::type;
7807 using root_implements_type = typename base_type::root_implements_type;
7808
7809 using base_type::base_type;
7810
7811 public:
7812
7813 using implements_type = implements;
7814 using IInspectable = Windows::Foundation::IInspectable;
7815
7816 weak_ref<D> get_weak()
7817 {
7818 return root_implements_type::template get_weak<D>();
7819 }
7820
7821 com_ptr<D> get_strong() noexcept
7822 {
7823 com_ptr<D> result;
7824 result.copy_from(static_cast<D*>(this));
7825 return result;
7826 }
7827
7828 template <typename T>
7829 auto get_abi(T const& value) const noexcept
7830 {
7831 return winrt::get_abi(value);
7832 }
7833
7834 template <typename T>
7835 void* get_abi() const noexcept
7836 {
7837 return static_cast<impl::producer_vtable<T>>(*this).value;
7838 }
7839
7840 operator IInspectable() const noexcept
7841 {
7842 IInspectable result;
7843 copy_from_abi(result, find_inspectable());
7844 return result;
7845 }
7846
7847 impl::hresult_type __stdcall QueryInterface(impl::guid_type const& id, void** object) noexcept
7848 {
7849 return root_implements_type::QueryInterface(reinterpret_cast<guid const&>(id), object);
7850 }
7851
7852 impl::count_type __stdcall AddRef() noexcept
7853 {
7854 return root_implements_type::AddRef();
7855 }
7856
7857 impl::count_type __stdcall Release() noexcept
7858 {
7859 return root_implements_type::Release();
7860 }
7861
7862 impl::hresult_type __stdcall GetIids(impl::count_type* count, impl::guid_type** iids) noexcept
7863 {
7864 return root_implements_type::GetIids(reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(count), reinterpret_cast<guid**>(iids));
7865 }
7866
7867 impl::hresult_type __stdcall GetRuntimeClassName(impl::hstring_type* value) noexcept
7868 {
7869 return root_implements_type::abi_GetRuntimeClassName(reinterpret_cast<void**>(value));
7870 }
7871
7872 using root_implements_type::GetTrustLevel;
7873
7874 impl::hresult_type __stdcall GetTrustLevel(impl::trust_level_type* value) noexcept
7875 {
7876 return root_implements_type::abi_GetTrustLevel(reinterpret_cast<Windows::Foundation::TrustLevel*>(value));
7877 }
7878
7879 void* find_interface(guid const& id) const noexcept override
7880 {
7881 return impl::find_iid(static_cast<const D*>(this), id);
7882 }
7883
7884 impl::inspectable_abi* find_inspectable() const noexcept override
7885 {
7886 return impl::find_inspectable(static_cast<const D*>(this));
7887 }
7888
7889 std::pair<uint32_t, const guid*> get_local_iids() const noexcept override
7890 {
7891 using interfaces = impl::uncloaked_interfaces<D>;
7892 using local_iids = impl::uncloaked_iids<interfaces>;
7893 return { static_cast<uint32_t>(local_iids::value.size()), local_iids::value.data() };
7894 }
7895
7896 private:
7897
7898 impl::unknown_abi* get_unknown() const noexcept override
7899 {
7900 return reinterpret_cast<impl::unknown_abi*>(to_abi<typename impl::implements_default_interface<D>::type>(this));
7901 }
7902
7903 hstring GetRuntimeClassName() const override
7904 {
7905 static_assert(std::is_base_of_v<implements_type, D>, "Class must derive from implements<> or ClassT<> where the first template parameter is the derived class name, e.g. struct D : implements<D, ...>");
7906 return impl::runtime_class_name<typename impl::implements_default_interface<D>::type>::get();
7907 }
7908
7909 template <typename, typename...>
7910 friend struct impl::root_implements;
7911
7912 template <typename T>
7913 friend struct weak_ref;
7914 };
7915}

7917namespace winrt::impl
7918{
7919 template <typename D>
7920 struct composable_factory
7921 {
7922 template <typename I, typename... Args>
7923 static I CreateInstance(const Windows::Foundation::IInspectable& outer, Windows::Foundation::IInspectable& inner, Args&&... args)
7924 {
7925 static_assert(std::is_base_of_v<Windows::Foundation::IInspectable, I>, "Requested interface must derive from winrt::Windows::Foundation::IInspectable");
7926 inner = CreateInstanceImpl(outer, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
7927 return inner.as<I>();
7928 }
7929
7930 private:
7931 template <typename... Args>
7932 static Windows::Foundation::IInspectable CreateInstanceImpl(const Windows::Foundation::IInspectable& outer, Args&&... args)
7933 {
7934 // Very specific dance here. The return value must have a ref on the outer, while inner must have a ref count of 1.
7935 // Be sure not to make a delegating QueryInterface call because the controlling outer is not fully constructed yet.
7936 com_ptr<D> instance = make_self<D>(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
7937 instance->m_outer = static_cast<inspectable_abi*>(get_abi(outer));
7938 Windows::Foundation::IInspectable inner;
7939 attach_abi(inner, to_abi<INonDelegatingInspectable>(detach_abi(instance)));
7940 return inner;
7941 }
7942 };
7943
7944 template <typename T, typename D, typename I>
7945 class __declspec(empty_bases) produce_dispatch_to_overridable_base
7946 {
7947 protected:
7948 D& shim() noexcept
7949 {
7950 return static_cast<T&>(*this).instance;
7951 }
7952
7953 I shim_overridable()
7954 {
7955 void* result{};
7956
7957 if (shim().outer())
7958 {
7959 check_hresult(shim().QueryInterface(guid_of<I>(), &result));
7960 }
7961
7962 return { result, take_ownership_from_abi };
7963 }
7964 };
7965
7966 template <typename T, typename D, typename I>
7967 struct produce_dispatch_to_overridable;
7968
7969 template <typename D, typename... I>
7970 class dispatch_to_overridable
7971 {
7972 class wrapper : public produce_dispatch_to_overridable<wrapper, D, I>...
7973 {
7974 D& instance;
7975
7976 template <typename, typename, typename>
7977 friend class produce_dispatch_to_overridable_base;
7978
7979 template <typename, typename...>
7980 friend class dispatch_to_overridable;
7981
7982 explicit wrapper(D& d) : instance(d) {}
7983
7984 public:
7985 wrapper(const wrapper&) = delete;
7986 wrapper(wrapper&&) = default;
7987 };
7988
7989 public:
7990 static wrapper overridable(D& instance) noexcept
7991 {
7992 return wrapper{ instance };
7993 }
7994 };
7995}

8174 struct file_time
8175 {
8176 uint64_t value{};
8177
8178 file_time() noexcept = default;
8179
8180 constexpr explicit file_time(uint64_t const value) noexcept : value(value)
8181 {
8182 }
8183
8184#ifdef _FILETIME_
8185 constexpr file_time(FILETIME const& value) noexcept
8186 : value(value.dwLowDateTime | (static_cast<uint64_t>(value.dwHighDateTime) << 32))
8187 {
8188 }
8189
8190 operator FILETIME() const noexcept
8191 {
8192 return { static_cast<DWORD>(value & 0xFFFFFFFF), static_cast<DWORD>(value >> 32) };
8193 }
8194#endif
8195 };

8197 struct clock
8198 {
8199 using rep = int64_t;
8200 using period = impl::filetime_period;
8201 using duration = Windows::Foundation::TimeSpan;
8202 using time_point = Windows::Foundation::DateTime;
8203
8204 static constexpr bool is_steady = false;
8205
8206 static time_point now() noexcept
8207 {
8208 file_time ft;
8209 WINRT_IMPL_GetSystemTimePreciseAsFileTime(&ft);
8210 return from_file_time(ft);
8211 }
8212
8213 static time_t to_time_t(time_point const& time) noexcept
8214 {
8215 return static_cast<time_t>(std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t(to_sys(time)));
8216 }
8217
8218 static time_point from_time_t(time_t time) noexcept
8219 {
8220 return from_sys(std::chrono::system_clock::from_time_t(time));
8221 }
8222
8223 static file_time to_file_time(time_point const& time) noexcept
8224 {
8225 return file_time{ static_cast<uint64_t>(time.time_since_epoch().count()) };
8226 }
8227
8228 static time_point from_file_time(file_time const& time) noexcept
8229 {
8230 return time_point{ duration{ time.value } };
8231 }
8232
8233 static auto to_FILETIME(time_point const& time) noexcept
8234 {
8235 return to_file_time(time);
8236 }
8237
8238 static time_point from_FILETIME(file_time const& time) noexcept
8239 {
8240 return from_file_time(time);
8241 }
8242
8243 template <typename Duration>
8244 static std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, std::common_type_t<Duration, std::chrono::seconds>>
8245 to_sys(std::chrono::time_point<clock, Duration> const& tp)
8246 {
8247 return epoch + tp.time_since_epoch();
8248 }
8249
8250 template <typename Duration>
8251 static std::chrono::time_point<clock, std::common_type_t<Duration, std::chrono::seconds>>
8252 from_sys(std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, Duration> const& tp)
8253 {
8254 using result_t = std::chrono::time_point<clock, std::common_type_t<Duration, std::chrono::seconds>>;
8255 return result_t{ tp - epoch };
8256 }
8257
8258 private:
8259
8260 // system_clock epoch is 00:00:00, Jan 1 1970.
8261 // This is 11644473600 seconds after Windows FILETIME epoch of 00:00:00, Jan 1 1601.
8262 static constexpr std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, std::chrono::seconds> epoch{ std::chrono::seconds{ -11644473600 } };
8263 };

8266WINRT_EXPORT namespace winrt
8267{
8268 struct access_token : handle
8269 {
8270 static access_token process()
8271 {
8272 access_token token;
8273 check_bool(WINRT_IMPL_OpenProcessToken(WINRT_IMPL_GetCurrentProcess(), 0x0002 /*TOKEN_DUPLICATE*/, token.put()));
8274 access_token duplicate;
8275 check_bool(WINRT_IMPL_DuplicateToken(token.get(), 2 /*SecurityImpersonation*/, duplicate.put()));
8276 return duplicate;
8277 }
8278
8279 static access_token thread()
8280 {
8281 access_token token;
8282
8283 if (!WINRT_IMPL_OpenThreadToken(WINRT_IMPL_GetCurrentThread(), 0x0004 /*TOKEN_IMPERSONATE*/, 1, token.put()))
8284 {
8285 uint32_t const error = WINRT_IMPL_GetLastError();
8286
8287 if (error != 1008 /*ERROR_NO_TOKEN*/)
8288 {
8289 throw_hresult(impl::hresult_from_win32(error));
8290 }
8291 }
8292
8293 return token;
8294 }
8295
8296 static access_token client()
8297 {
8298 struct impersonate_guard
8299 {
8300 impersonate_guard(com_ptr<impl::IServerSecurity> const& server) : m_server(server)
8301 {
8302 check_hresult(m_server->ImpersonateClient());
8303 }
8304
8305 ~impersonate_guard()
8306 {
8307 check_hresult(m_server->RevertToSelf());
8308 }
8309
8310 private:
8311
8312 com_ptr<impl::IServerSecurity> const& m_server;
8313 };
8314
8315 auto server = capture<impl::IServerSecurity>(WINRT_IMPL_CoGetCallContext);
8316 impersonate_guard impersonate(server);
8317 return thread();
8318 }
8319
8320 access_token() = default;
8321 access_token(access_token&& other) = default;
8322 access_token& operator=(access_token&& other) = default;
8323
8324 access_token impersonate() const
8325 {
8326 auto previous = thread();
8327 check_bool(WINRT_IMPL_SetThreadToken(nullptr, get()));
8328 return previous;
8329 }
8330
8331 void revert() const
8332 {
8333 check_bool(WINRT_IMPL_SetThreadToken(nullptr, get()));
8334 }
8335
8336 auto operator()() const
8337 {
8338 struct guard
8339 {
8340 guard(access_token&& previous) noexcept : m_previous(std::move(previous))
8341 {
8342 }
8343
8344 ~guard()
8345 {
8346 m_previous.revert();
8347 }
8348
8349 guard(guard const&)
8350 {
8351 // A Visual C++ compiler bug (550631) requires the copy constructor even though it is never called.
8352 WINRT_ASSERT(false);
8353 }
8354
8355 private:
8356
8357 access_token const m_previous;
8358 };
8359
8360 return guard(impersonate());
8361 }
8362 };
8363}

8365namespace winrt::impl
8366{
8367 inline size_t hash_data(void const* ptr, size_t const bytes) noexcept
8368 {
8369#ifdef _WIN64
8370 constexpr size_t fnv_offset_basis = 14695981039346656037ULL;
8371 constexpr size_t fnv_prime = 1099511628211ULL;
8372#else
8373 constexpr size_t fnv_offset_basis = 2166136261U;
8374 constexpr size_t fnv_prime = 16777619U;
8375#endif
8376 size_t result = fnv_offset_basis;
8377 uint8_t const* const buffer = static_cast<uint8_t const*>(ptr);
8378
8379 for (size_t next = 0; next < bytes; ++next)
8380 {
8381 result ^= buffer[next];
8382 result *= fnv_prime;
8383 }
8384
8385 return result;
8386 }
8387
8388 struct hash_base
8389 {
8390 size_t operator()(Windows::Foundation::IUnknown const& value) const noexcept
8391 {
8392 void* const abi_value = get_abi(value.try_as<Windows::Foundation::IUnknown>());
8393 return std::hash<void*>{}(abi_value);
8394 }
8395 };
8396}

8410 template<> struct hash<winrt::Windows::Foundation::IActivationFactory> : winrt::impl::hash_base {};

8417 }
8418 };

8423 template <typename T>
8424 struct fast_iterator
8425 {
8426 using iterator_concept = std::random_access_iterator_tag;
8427 using iterator_category = std::input_iterator_tag;
8428 using value_type = decltype(std::declval<T>().GetAt(0));
8429 using difference_type = ptrdiff_t;
8430 using pointer = void;
8431 using reference = value_type;
8432
8433 fast_iterator() noexcept = default;
8434
8435 fast_iterator(T const& collection, uint32_t const index) noexcept :
8436 m_collection(&collection),
8437 m_index(index)
8438 {}
8439
8440 fast_iterator& operator++() noexcept
8441 {
8442 ++m_index;
8443 return *this;
8444 }
8445
8446 fast_iterator operator++(int) noexcept
8447 {
8448 auto previous = *this;
8449 ++m_index;
8450 return previous;
8451 }
8452
8453 fast_iterator& operator--() noexcept
8454 {
8455 --m_index;
8456 return *this;
8457 }
8458
8459 fast_iterator operator--(int) noexcept
8460 {
8461 auto previous = *this;
8462 --m_index;
8463 return previous;
8464 }
8465
8466 fast_iterator& operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept
8467 {
8468 m_index += static_cast<uint32_t>(n);
8469 return *this;
8470 }
8471
8472 fast_iterator operator+(difference_type n) const noexcept
8473 {
8474 return fast_iterator(*this) += n;
8475 }
8476
8477 fast_iterator& operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept
8478 {
8479 return *this += -n;
8480 }
8481
8482 fast_iterator operator-(difference_type n) const noexcept
8483 {
8484 return *this + -n;
8485 }
8486
8487 difference_type operator-(fast_iterator const& other) const noexcept
8488 {
8489 WINRT_ASSERT(m_collection == other.m_collection);
8490 return static_cast<difference_type>(m_index) - static_cast<difference_type>(other.m_index);
8491 }
8492
8493 reference operator*() const
8494 {
8495 return m_collection->GetAt(m_index);
8496 }
8497
8498 reference operator[](difference_type n) const
8499 {
8500 return m_collection->GetAt(m_index + static_cast<uint32_t>(n));
8501 }
8502
8503 bool operator==(fast_iterator const& other) const noexcept
8504 {
8505 WINRT_ASSERT(m_collection == other.m_collection);
8506 return m_index == other.m_index;
8507 }
8508
8509 bool operator<(fast_iterator const& other) const noexcept
8510 {
8511 WINRT_ASSERT(m_collection == other.m_collection);
8512 return m_index < other.m_index;
8513 }
8514
8515 bool operator>(fast_iterator const& other) const noexcept
8516 {
8517 WINRT_ASSERT(m_collection == other.m_collection);
8518 return m_index > other.m_index;
8519 }
8520
8521 bool operator!=(fast_iterator const& other) const noexcept
8522 {
8523 return !(*this == other);
8524 }
8525
8526 bool operator<=(fast_iterator const& other) const noexcept
8527 {
8528 return !(*this > other);
8529 }
8530
8531 bool operator>=(fast_iterator const& other) const noexcept
8532 {
8533 return !(*this < other);
8534 }
8535
8536 friend fast_iterator operator+(difference_type n, fast_iterator it) noexcept
8537 {
8538 return it + n;
8539 }
8540
8541 friend fast_iterator operator-(difference_type n, fast_iterator it) noexcept
8542 {
8543 return it - n;
8544 }
8545
8546 private:
8547
8548 T const* m_collection = nullptr;
8549 uint32_t m_index = 0;
8550 };
8551
8552 template <typename T>
8553 class has_GetAt
8554 {
8555 template <typename U, typename = decltype(std::declval<U>().GetAt(0))> static constexpr bool get_value(int) { return true; }
8556 template <typename> static constexpr bool get_value(...) { return false; }
8557
8558 public:
8559
8560 static constexpr bool value = get_value<T>(0);
8561 };
8562
8563 template <typename T, std::enable_if_t<!has_GetAt<T>::value, int> = 0>
8564 auto get_begin_iterator(T const& collection) -> decltype(collection.First())
8565 {
8566 auto result = collection.First();
8567
8568 if (!result.HasCurrent())
8569 {
8570 return {};
8571 }
8572
8573 return result;
8574 }
8575
8576 template <typename T, std::enable_if_t<!has_GetAt<T>::value, int> = 0>
8577 auto get_end_iterator([[maybe_unused]] T const& collection) noexcept -> decltype(collection.First())
8578 {
8579 return {};
8580 }
8581
8582 template <typename T, std::enable_if_t<has_GetAt<T>::value, int> = 0>
8583 fast_iterator<T> get_begin_iterator(T const& collection) noexcept
8584 {
8585 return { collection, 0 };
8586 }
8587
8588 template <typename T, std::enable_if_t<has_GetAt<T>::value, int> = 0>
8589 fast_iterator<T> get_end_iterator(T const& collection)
8590 {
8591 return { collection, collection.Size() };
8592 }
8593
8594 template <typename T, std::enable_if_t<has_GetAt<T>::value, int> = 0>
8595 auto rbegin(T const& collection)
8596 {
8597 return std::make_reverse_iterator(get_end_iterator(collection));
8598 }
8599
8600 template <typename T, std::enable_if_t<has_GetAt<T>::value, int> = 0>
8601 auto rend(T const& collection)
8602 {
8603 return std::make_reverse_iterator(get_begin_iterator(collection));
8604 }
8605
8606 using std::begin;
8607 using std::end;
8608}

8612 inline auto submit_threadpool_callback(void(__stdcall* callback)(void*, void* context), void* context)
8613 {
8614 if (!WINRT_IMPL_TrySubmitThreadpoolCallback(callback, context, nullptr))
8615 {
8616 throw_last_error();
8617 }
8618 }
8619
8620 inline void __stdcall resume_background_callback(void*, void* context) noexcept
8621 {
8622 coroutine_handle<>::from_address(context)();
8623 };
8624
8625 inline auto resume_background(coroutine_handle<> handle)
8626 {
8627 submit_threadpool_callback(resume_background_callback, handle.address());
8628 }
8629
8630 inline std::pair<int32_t, int32_t> get_apartment_type() noexcept
8631 {
8632 int32_t aptType;
8633 int32_t aptTypeQualifier;
8634 if (0 == WINRT_IMPL_CoGetApartmentType(&aptType, &aptTypeQualifier))
8635 {
8636 return { aptType, aptTypeQualifier };
8637 }
8638 else
8639 {
8640 return { 1 /* APTTYPE_MTA */, 1 /* APTTYPEQUALIFIER_IMPLICIT_MTA */ };
8641 }
8642 }
8643
8644 inline bool is_sta_thread() noexcept
8645 {
8646 auto type = get_apartment_type();
8647 switch (type.first)
8648 {
8649 case 0: /* APTTYPE_STA */
8650 case 3: /* APTTYPE_MAINSTA */
8651 return true;
8652 case 2: /* APTTYPE_NA */
8653 return type.second == 3 /* APTTYPEQUALIFIER_NA_ON_STA */ ||
8654 type.second == 5 /* APTTYPEQUALIFIER_NA_ON_MAINSTA */;
8655 }
8656 return false;
8657 }
8658
8659 struct resume_apartment_context
8660 {
8661 resume_apartment_context() = default;
8662 resume_apartment_context(std::nullptr_t) : m_context(nullptr), m_context_type(-1) {}
8663 resume_apartment_context(resume_apartment_context const&) = default;
8664 resume_apartment_context(resume_apartment_context&& other) noexcept :
8665 m_context(std::move(other.m_context)), m_context_type(std::exchange(other.m_context_type, -1)) {}
8666 resume_apartment_context& operator=(resume_apartment_context const&) = default;
8667 resume_apartment_context& operator=(resume_apartment_context&& other) noexcept
8668 {
8669 m_context = std::move(other.m_context);
8670 m_context_type = std::exchange(other.m_context_type, -1);
8671 return *this;
8672 }
8673 bool valid() const noexcept
8674 {
8675 return m_context_type >= 0;
8676 }
8677
8678 com_ptr<IContextCallback> m_context = try_capture<IContextCallback>(WINRT_IMPL_CoGetObjectContext);
8679 int32_t m_context_type = get_apartment_type().first;
8680 };
8681
8682 inline int32_t __stdcall resume_apartment_callback(com_callback_args* args) noexcept
8683 {
8684 coroutine_handle<>::from_address(args->data)();
8685 return 0;
8686 };
8687
8688 inline void resume_apartment_sync(com_ptr<IContextCallback> const& context, coroutine_handle<> handle)
8689 {
8690 com_callback_args args{};
8691 args.data = handle.address();
8692
8693 check_hresult(context->ContextCallback(resume_apartment_callback, &args, guid_of<ICallbackWithNoReentrancyToApplicationSTA>(), 5, nullptr));
8694 }
8695
8696 struct threadpool_resume
8697 {
8698 threadpool_resume(com_ptr<IContextCallback> const& context, coroutine_handle<> handle) :
8699 m_context(context), m_handle(handle) { }
8700 com_ptr<IContextCallback> m_context;
8701 coroutine_handle<> m_handle;
8702 };
8703
8704 inline void __stdcall fallback_submit_threadpool_callback(void*, void* p) noexcept
8705 {
8706 std::unique_ptr<threadpool_resume> state{ static_cast<threadpool_resume*>(p) };
8707 resume_apartment_sync(state->m_context, state->m_handle);
8708 }
8709
8710 inline void resume_apartment_on_threadpool(com_ptr<IContextCallback> const& context, coroutine_handle<> handle)
8711 {
8712 auto state = std::make_unique<threadpool_resume>(context, handle);
8713 submit_threadpool_callback(fallback_submit_threadpool_callback, state.get());
8714 state.release();
8715 }
8716
8717 inline auto resume_apartment(resume_apartment_context const& context, coroutine_handle<> handle)
8718 {
8719 WINRT_ASSERT(context.valid());
8720 if ((context.m_context == nullptr) || (context.m_context == try_capture<IContextCallback>(WINRT_IMPL_CoGetObjectContext)))
8721 {
8722 handle();
8723 }
8724 else if (context.m_context_type == 1 /* APTTYPE_MTA */)
8725 {
8726 resume_background(handle);
8727 }
8728 else if (is_sta_thread())
8729 {
8730 resume_apartment_on_threadpool(context.m_context, handle);
8731 }
8732 else
8733 {
8734 resume_apartment_sync(context.m_context, handle);
8735 }
8736 }
8737
8738 template <typename T>
8739 class awaiter_finder
8740 {
8741 template <typename> static constexpr bool find_awaitable_member(...) { return false; }
8742 template <typename> static constexpr bool find_co_await_member(...) { return false; }
8743 template <typename> static constexpr bool find_co_await_free(...) { return false; }
8744
8745#ifdef WINRT_IMPL_COROUTINES
8746 template <typename U, typename = decltype(std::declval<U>().await_ready())> static constexpr bool find_awaitable_member(int) { return true; }
8747 template <typename U, typename = decltype(std::declval<U>().operator co_await())> static constexpr bool find_co_await_member(int) { return true; }
8748 template <typename U, typename = decltype(operator co_await(std::declval<U>()))> static constexpr bool find_co_await_free(int) { return true; }
8749#endif
8750
8751 public:
8752
8753 static constexpr bool has_awaitable_member = find_awaitable_member<T>(0);
8754 static constexpr bool has_co_await_member = find_co_await_member<T&&>(0);
8755 static constexpr bool has_co_await_free = find_co_await_free<T&&>(0);
8756 };
8757}
8758
8759WINRT_EXPORT namespace winrt
8760{
8761 struct cancellable_promise
8762 {
8763 using canceller_t = void(*)(void*);
8764
8765 void set_canceller(canceller_t canceller, void* context)
8766 {
8767 m_context = context;
8768 m_canceller.store(canceller, std::memory_order_release);
8769 }
8770
8771 void revoke_canceller()
8772 {
8773 while (m_canceller.exchange(nullptr, std::memory_order_acquire) == cancelling_ptr)
8774 {
8775 std::this_thread::yield();
8776 }
8777 }
8778
8779 void cancel()
8780 {
8781 auto canceller = m_canceller.exchange(cancelling_ptr, std::memory_order_acquire);
8782 struct unique_cancellation_lock
8783 {
8784 cancellable_promise* promise;
8785 ~unique_cancellation_lock()
8786 {
8787 promise->m_canceller.store(nullptr, std::memory_order_release);
8788 }
8789 } lock{ this };
8790
8791 if ((canceller != nullptr) && (canceller != cancelling_ptr))
8792 {
8793 canceller(m_context);
8794 }
8795 }
8796
8797 private:
8798 static inline auto const cancelling_ptr = reinterpret_cast<canceller_t>(1);
8799
8800 std::atomic<canceller_t> m_canceller{ nullptr };
8801 void* m_context{ nullptr };
8802 };
8803
8804 struct enable_await_cancellation
8805 {
8806 enable_await_cancellation() noexcept = default;
8807 enable_await_cancellation(enable_await_cancellation const&) = default;
8808
8809 ~enable_await_cancellation()
8810 {
8811 if (m_promise)
8812 {
8813 m_promise->revoke_canceller();
8814 }
8815 }
8816
8817 void operator=(enable_await_cancellation const&) = delete;
8818
8819 void set_cancellable_promise(cancellable_promise* promise) noexcept
8820 {
8821 m_promise = promise;
8822 }
8823
8824 private:
8825
8826 cancellable_promise* m_promise = nullptr;
8827 };
8828}

8830namespace winrt::impl
8831{
8832 template <typename T>
8833 decltype(auto) get_awaiter(T&& value) noexcept
8834 {
8835#ifdef WINRT_IMPL_COROUTINES
8836 if constexpr (awaiter_finder<T>::has_co_await_member)
8837 {
8838 static_assert(!awaiter_finder<T>::has_co_await_free, "Ambiguous operator co_await (as both member and free function).");
8839 return static_cast<T&&>(value).operator co_await();
8840 }
8841 else if constexpr (awaiter_finder<T>::has_co_await_free)
8842 {
8843 return operator co_await(static_cast<T&&>(value));
8844 }
8845 else
8846 {
8847 static_assert(awaiter_finder<T>::has_awaitable_member, "Not an awaitable type");
8848 return static_cast<T&&>(value);
8849 }
8850#else
8851 return static_cast<T&&>(value);
8852#endif
8853 }
8854
8855 template <typename T>
8856 struct notify_awaiter
8857 {
8858 decltype(get_awaiter(std::declval<T&&>())) awaitable;
8859
8860 notify_awaiter(T&& awaitable_arg, [[maybe_unused]] cancellable_promise* promise = nullptr) : awaitable(get_awaiter(static_cast<T&&>(awaitable_arg)))
8861 {
8862 if constexpr (std::is_convertible_v<std::remove_reference_t<decltype(awaitable)>&, enable_await_cancellation&>)
8863 {
8864 if (promise)
8865 {
8866 static_cast<enable_await_cancellation&>(awaitable).set_cancellable_promise(promise);
8867 awaitable.enable_cancellation(promise);
8868 }
8869 }
8870 }
8871
8872 bool await_ready()
8873 {
8874 if (winrt_suspend_handler)
8875 {
8876 winrt_suspend_handler(this);
8877 }
8878
8879 return awaitable.await_ready();
8880 }
8881
8882 template <typename U>
8883 auto await_suspend(coroutine_handle<U> handle)
8884 {
8885 return awaitable.await_suspend(handle);
8886 }
8887
8888 decltype(auto) await_resume()
8889 {
8890 if (winrt_resume_handler)
8891 {
8892 winrt_resume_handler(this);
8893 }
8894
8895 return awaitable.await_resume();
8896 }
8897 };
8898}

8994 [[nodiscard]] inline auto resume_after(Windows::Foundation::TimeSpan duration) noexcept
8995 {
8996 struct awaitable : enable_await_cancellation
8997 {
8998 explicit awaitable(Windows::Foundation::TimeSpan duration) noexcept :
8999 m_duration(duration)
9000 {
9001 }
9002
9003 void enable_cancellation(cancellable_promise* promise)
9004 {
9005 promise->set_canceller([](void* context)
9006 {
9007 auto that = static_cast<awaitable*>(context);
9008 if (that->m_state.exchange(state::canceled, std::memory_order_acquire) == state::pending)
9009 {
9010 that->fire_immediately();
9011 }
9012 }, this);
9013 }
9014
9015 bool await_ready() const noexcept
9016 {
9017 return m_duration.count() <= 0;
9018 }
9019
9020 void await_suspend(impl::coroutine_handle<> handle)
9021 {
9022 m_handle = handle;
9023 m_timer.attach(check_pointer(WINRT_IMPL_CreateThreadpoolTimer(callback, this, nullptr)));
9024 int64_t relative_count = -m_duration.count();
9025 WINRT_IMPL_SetThreadpoolTimer(m_timer.get(), &relative_count, 0, 0);
9026
9027 state expected = state::idle;
9028 if (!m_state.compare_exchange_strong(expected, state::pending, std::memory_order_release))
9029 {
9030 fire_immediately();
9031 }
9032 }
9033
9034 void await_resume()
9035 {
9036 if (m_state.exchange(state::idle, std::memory_order_relaxed) == state::canceled)
9037 {
9038 throw hresult_canceled();
9039 }
9040 }
9041
9042 private:
9043
9044 static int32_t __stdcall fallback_SetThreadpoolTimerEx(winrt::impl::ptp_timer, void*, uint32_t, uint32_t) noexcept
9045 {
9046 return 0; // pretend timer has already triggered and a callback is on its way
9047 }
9048
9049 void fire_immediately() noexcept
9050 {
9051 static int32_t(__stdcall* handler)(winrt::impl::ptp_timer, void*, uint32_t, uint32_t) noexcept;
9052 impl::load_runtime_function(L"kernel32.dll", "SetThreadpoolTimerEx", handler, fallback_SetThreadpoolTimerEx);
9053
9054 if (handler(m_timer.get(), nullptr, 0, 0))
9055 {
9056 int64_t now = 0;
9057 WINRT_IMPL_SetThreadpoolTimer(m_timer.get(), &now, 0, 0);
9058 }
9059 }
9060
9061 static void __stdcall callback(void*, void* context, void*) noexcept
9062 {
9063 auto that = reinterpret_cast<awaitable*>(context);
9064 that->m_handle();
9065 }
9066
9067 struct timer_traits
9068 {
9069 using type = impl::ptp_timer;
9070
9071 static void close(type value) noexcept
9072 {
9073 WINRT_IMPL_CloseThreadpoolTimer(value);
9074 }
9075
9076 static constexpr type invalid() noexcept
9077 {
9078 return nullptr;
9079 }
9080 };
9081
9082 enum class state { idle, pending, canceled };
9083
9084 handle_type<timer_traits> m_timer;
9085 Windows::Foundation::TimeSpan m_duration;
9086 impl::coroutine_handle<> m_handle;
9087 std::atomic<state> m_state{ state::idle };
9088 };
9089
9090 return awaitable{ duration };
9091 }

9100 [[nodiscard]] inline auto resume_on_signal(void* handle, Windows::Foundation::TimeSpan timeout = {}) noexcept
9101 {
9102 struct awaitable : enable_await_cancellation
9103 {
9104 awaitable(void* handle, Windows::Foundation::TimeSpan timeout) noexcept :
9105 m_timeout(timeout),
9106 m_handle(handle)
9107 {}
9108
9109 void enable_cancellation(cancellable_promise* promise)
9110 {
9111 promise->set_canceller([](void* context)
9112 {
9113 auto that = static_cast<awaitable*>(context);
9114 if (that->m_state.exchange(state::canceled, std::memory_order_acquire) == state::pending)
9115 {
9116 that->fire_immediately();
9117 }
9118 }, this);
9119 }
9120
9121 bool await_ready() const noexcept
9122 {
9123 return WINRT_IMPL_WaitForSingleObject(m_handle, 0) == 0;
9124 }
9125
9126 void await_suspend(impl::coroutine_handle<> resume)
9127 {
9128 m_resume = resume;
9129 m_wait.attach(check_pointer(WINRT_IMPL_CreateThreadpoolWait(callback, this, nullptr)));
9130 int64_t relative_count = -m_timeout.count();
9131 int64_t* file_time = relative_count != 0 ? &relative_count : nullptr;
9132 WINRT_IMPL_SetThreadpoolWait(m_wait.get(), m_handle, file_time);
9133
9134 state expected = state::idle;
9135 if (!m_state.compare_exchange_strong(expected, state::pending, std::memory_order_release))
9136 {
9137 fire_immediately();
9138 }
9139 }
9140
9141 bool await_resume()
9142 {
9143 if (m_state.exchange(state::idle, std::memory_order_relaxed) == state::canceled)
9144 {
9145 throw hresult_canceled();
9146 }
9147 return m_result == 0;
9148 }
9149
9150 private:
9151 static int32_t __stdcall fallback_SetThreadpoolWaitEx(winrt::impl::ptp_wait, void*, void*, void*) noexcept
9152 {
9153 return 0; // pretend wait has already triggered and a callback is on its way
9154 }
9155
9156 void fire_immediately() noexcept
9157 {
9158 static int32_t(__stdcall* handler)(winrt::impl::ptp_wait, void*, void*, void*) noexcept;
9159 impl::load_runtime_function(L"kernel32.dll", "SetThreadpoolWaitEx", handler, fallback_SetThreadpoolWaitEx);
9160
9161 if (handler(m_wait.get(), nullptr, nullptr, nullptr))
9162 {
9163 int64_t now = 0;
9164 WINRT_IMPL_SetThreadpoolWait(m_wait.get(), WINRT_IMPL_GetCurrentProcess(), &now);
9165 }
9166 }
9167
9168 static void __stdcall callback(void*, void* context, void*, uint32_t result) noexcept
9169 {
9170 auto that = static_cast<awaitable*>(context);
9171 that->m_result = result;
9172 that->m_resume();
9173 }
9174
9175 struct wait_traits
9176 {
9177 using type = impl::ptp_wait;
9178
9179 static void close(type value) noexcept
9180 {
9181 WINRT_IMPL_CloseThreadpoolWait(value);
9182 }
9183
9184 static constexpr type invalid() noexcept
9185 {
9186 return nullptr;
9187 }
9188 };
9189
9190 enum class state { idle, pending, canceled };
9191
9192 handle_type<wait_traits> m_wait;
9193 Windows::Foundation::TimeSpan m_timeout;
9194 void* m_handle;
9195 uint32_t m_result{};
9196 impl::coroutine_handle<> m_resume{ nullptr };
9197 std::atomic<state> m_state{ state::idle };
9198 };
9199
9200 return awaitable{ handle, timeout };
9201 }

9203 struct thread_pool
9204 {
9205 thread_pool() :
9206 m_pool(check_pointer(WINRT_IMPL_CreateThreadpool(nullptr)))
9207 {
9208 m_environment.Pool = m_pool.get();
9209 }
9210
9211 void thread_limits(uint32_t const high, uint32_t const low)
9212 {
9213 WINRT_IMPL_SetThreadpoolThreadMaximum(m_pool.get(), high);
9214 check_bool(WINRT_IMPL_SetThreadpoolThreadMinimum(m_pool.get(), low));
9215 }
9216
9217 bool await_ready() const noexcept

9340
9341namespace winrt::impl
9342{
9343 struct natvis
9344 {
9345 static auto __stdcall abi_val(void* object, wchar_t const * iid_str, int method)
9346 {
9347 union variant
9348 {
9349 bool b;
9350 wchar_t c;
9351 int8_t i1;
9352 int16_t i2;
9353 int32_t i4;
9354 int64_t i8;
9355 uint8_t u1;
9356 uint16_t u2;
9357 uint32_t u4;
9358 uint64_t u8;
9359 float r4;
9360 double r8;
9361 guid g;
9362 void* s;
9363 uint8_t v[1024];
9364 }
9365 value;
9366 value.s = 0;
9367 guid iid;
9368 if (WINRT_IMPL_IIDFromString(iid_str, &iid) == 0)
9369 {
9370 struct memory_basic_information
9371 {
9372 void* base_address;
9373 void* allocation_base;
9374 uint32_t allocation_protect;
9375#ifdef _WIN64
9376 uint32_t __alignment1;
9377#endif
9378 uintptr_t region_size;
9379 uint32_t state;
9380 uint32_t protect;
9381 uint32_t type;
9382#ifdef _WIN64
9383 uint32_t __alignment2;
9384#endif
9385 };
9386 memory_basic_information info;
9387 // validate object pointer is readable
9388 if ((WINRT_IMPL_VirtualQuery(object, &info, sizeof(info)) != 0) && ((info.protect & 0xEE) != 0))
9389 {
9390 inspectable_abi* pinsp;
9391 if (((unknown_abi*)object)->QueryInterface(iid, reinterpret_cast<void**>(&pinsp)) == 0)
9392 {
9393 static const int IInspectable_vtbl_size = 6;
9394 auto vtbl = *(void***)pinsp;
9395 // validate vtbl pointer is readable
9396 if ((WINRT_IMPL_VirtualQuery(vtbl, &info, sizeof(info)) != 0) && ((info.protect & 0xEE) != 0))
9397 {
9398 auto vfunc = vtbl[method + IInspectable_vtbl_size];
9399 // validate method pointer is executable
9400 if ((WINRT_IMPL_VirtualQuery(vfunc, &info, sizeof(info)) != 0) && ((info.protect & 0xF0) != 0))
9401 {
9402 typedef int32_t(__stdcall inspectable_abi:: * PropertyAccessor)(void*);
9403 (pinsp->**(PropertyAccessor*)&vfunc)(&value);
9404 pinsp->Release();
9405 }
9406 }
9407 }
9408 }
9409 }
9410 return value;
9411 }
9412
9413 static auto __stdcall get_val(winrt::Windows::Foundation::IInspectable* object, wchar_t const* iid_str, int method)
9414 {
9415 return abi_val(static_cast<unknown_abi*>(get_abi(*object)), iid_str, method);
9416 }
9417 };
9418}

9453WINRT_EXPORT namespace winrt
9454{
9455 template <size_t BaseSize, size_t ComponentSize>
9456 constexpr bool check_version(char const(&base)[BaseSize], char const(&component)[ComponentSize]) noexcept
9457 {
9458 if constexpr (BaseSize != ComponentSize)
9459 {
9460 return false;
9461 }
9462
9463 for (size_t i = 0; i != BaseSize - 1; ++i)
9464 {
9465 if (base[i] != component[i])
9466 {
9467 return false;
9468 }
9469 }
9470
9471 return true;
9472 }
9473}
